WEBVTT

1
00:00:34.552 --> 00:00:38.498
Report to your stations immediately. This is not a drill.

2
00:00:38.643 --> 00:00:40.004
We are under attack.

3
00:00:41.237 --> 00:00:42.598
We are under attack.

4
00:01:44.106 --> 00:01:45.467
- Shit!
- Language!

5
00:01:46.876 --> 00:01:48.761
Jarvis. what's the view from upstairs?

6
00:01:48.878 --> 00:01:51.123
The central building is protected by some kind of energy shield.

7
00:01:52.348 --> 00:01:57.110
Strucker's technology is well beyond any other Hydra base we've taken.

8
00:01:59.320 --> 00:02:04.194
Loki's scepter must be here.  Strucker couldn't mount this defense without it.

9
00:02:04.231 --> 00:02:05.115
At long last.

10
00:02:17.376 --> 00:02:20.369
At long last is lasting a little long. boys.

11
00:02:24.180 --> 00:02:27.445
Yeah.  I think we've lost the element of surprise.

12
00:02:29.421 --> 00:02:33.075
Wait a second.  No one else is going to deal with the fact that Cap just said "language?"

13
00:02:33.121 --> 00:02:33.621
I know.

14
00:02:39.987 --> 00:02:41.348
It just slipped out.

15
00:02:47.950 --> 00:02:49.051
Who gave the order to attack?

16
00:02:49.129 --> 00:02:54.992
Herr Strucker. it's the Avengers.  They landed in the far woods. the perimeter guard panicked.

17
00:02:55.053 --> 00:02:57.298
They have to be after the scepter.

18
00:02:58.182 --> 00:03:00.243
- Can we hold them?
- They are the Avengers!

19
00:03:00.343 --> 00:03:02.291
- Deploy the rest of the tanks.
- Yes. sir.

20
00:03:02.584 --> 00:03:07.118
Concentrate fire on the weak ones.  A hit can make them close ranks.

21
00:03:08.526 --> 00:03:11.372
Everything we've accomplished...we're on the verge of our greatest breakthrough...

22
00:03:11.558 --> 00:03:14.551
Then let's show them what we've accomplished.

23
00:03:14.764 --> 00:03:16.057
Send out the twins.

24
00:03:17.542 --> 00:03:18.494
It's too soon.

25
00:03:18.532 --> 00:03:20.505
It's what they signed up for.

26
00:03:21.240 --> 00:03:22.669
My men can hold them.

27
00:03:31.282 --> 00:03:33.459
Sir. the city is taking fire.

28
00:03:36.185 --> 00:03:40.003
Well. we know Strucker's not going to worry about civilian casualties.

29
00:03:40.376 --> 00:03:42.009
Send in the Iron Legion.

30
00:03:46.661 --> 00:03:49.586
This quadrant is unsafe.  Please back away.

31
00:03:50.331 --> 00:03:51.692
We are here to help.

32
00:03:52.934 --> 00:03:55.634
This quadrant is unsafe.  Please back away.

33
00:03:56.394 --> 00:03:57.550
Please back away.

34
00:03:58.173 --> 00:04:02.868
We wish to avoid collateral damage and will inform you when this current conflict is resolved.

35
00:04:02.943 --> 00:04:04.304
We are here to help.

36
00:04:06.849 --> 00:04:08.210
We are here to help.

37
00:04:09.821 --> 00:04:11.045
We will not yield.

38
00:04:11.756 --> 00:04:15.157
The Americans sent their circus freaks to test us.

39
00:04:15.758 --> 00:04:17.867
We will send them back in bags.

40
00:04:20.594 --> 00:04:22.771
- No Surrender!
- No Surrender!

41
00:04:24.903 --> 00:04:26.468
I am going to surrender.

42
00:04:27.002 --> 00:04:32.085
You will delete everything.  If we give the Avengers the weapons. they may not look too far into what we've been...

43
00:04:32.177 --> 00:04:34.294
- The twins!
- They are not ready to take on...

44
00:04:34.476 --> 00:04:36.913
No. no. I mean...the twins!

45
00:05:04.708 --> 00:05:06.545
You didn't see that coming?

46
00:05:13.449 --> 00:05:14.249
Clint!

47
00:05:17.803 --> 00:05:18.748
We have an enhanced in the field.

48
00:05:18.830 --> 00:05:19.646
Clint's hit!

49
00:05:24.293 --> 00:05:26.246
Somebody want to deal with that bunker?

50
00:05:29.999 --> 00:05:30.679
Thank you.

51
00:05:37.807 --> 00:05:40.596
Stark. we're going to need to get inside.

52
00:05:41.410 --> 00:05:42.430
I'm closing in.

53
00:05:45.548 --> 00:05:47.317
Jarvis. am I?  Closing in?

54
00:05:48.365 --> 00:05:49.862
You see a power source for that shield?

55
00:05:50.385 --> 00:05:52.330
There's a pathway. below the north tower.

56
00:05:52.522 --> 00:05:55.583
Great. I wanna poke it with something.

57
00:06:02.462 --> 00:06:03.686
Drawbridge is down. people.

58
00:06:08.605 --> 00:06:10.489
- The enhanced?
- He's a blur.

59
00:06:11.138 --> 00:06:12.538
All the new player's we've faced. I've never seen this.

60
00:06:13.709 --> 00:06:15.410
In fact. I still haven't.

61
00:06:15.676 --> 00:06:18.181
Clint's hit pretty bad. guys.  We're gonna need evac.

62
00:06:18.270 --> 00:06:20.170
I can get Barton to the jet.  The sooner we're gone the better.

63
00:06:21.182 --> 00:06:22.682
- You and Stark secure the scepter.
- Copy that.

64
00:06:24.987 --> 00:06:28.660
- It looks like they're lining up.
- Well. they're excited.

65
00:06:31.921 --> 00:06:33.077
Find the scepter.

66
00:06:33.715 --> 00:06:36.436
And for gosh sake. watch your language!

67
00:06:37.932 --> 00:06:39.420
That's not going away anytime soon.

68
00:06:45.341 --> 00:06:47.641
Guys. stop. we gotta talk this through.

69
00:06:51.566 --> 00:06:53.539
- It was a good talk.
- No it wasn't.

70
00:06:59.854 --> 00:07:00.854
Sentry mode.

71
00:07:04.043 --> 00:07:05.543
Okay Jarvis.  You know I want it all.

72
00:07:06.598 --> 00:07:07.998
Make sure you copy Hill at HQ.

73
00:07:11.936 --> 00:07:13.636
We're locked down out here.

74
00:07:14.972 --> 00:07:17.421
Then get to Banner.  Time for a lullaby.

75
00:07:19.943 --> 00:07:22.392
I know you're hiding more than files.

76
00:07:23.197 --> 00:07:25.397
Hey. J.  Gimme an IR scan of the room real quick.

77
00:07:25.794 --> 00:07:30.794
The wall to your left...I'm reading steel reinforcement and an air current.

78
00:07:32.878 --> 00:07:35.890
Please be a secret door. please be a secret door. please be a secret door...

79
00:07:36.738 --> 00:07:37.738
Yay!

80
00:07:53.611 --> 00:07:54.427
Hey big guy.

81
00:07:58.583 --> 00:07:59.739
The sun's getting real low.

82
00:09:03.314 --> 00:09:04.334
Baron Strucker.

83
00:09:05.515 --> 00:09:07.148
Hydra's number one thug.

84
00:09:08.018 --> 00:09:10.399
Technically. I'm a thug for SHIELD.

85
00:09:11.313 --> 00:09:13.918
Well then technically you're unemployed.  Where's Loki's scepter?

86
00:09:15.224 --> 00:09:17.537
Don't worry. I know when I'm beat.

87
00:09:18.127 --> 00:09:20.648
You'll mention how I cooperated. I hope.

88
00:09:20.784 --> 00:09:24.085
I'll put it right under illegal human experimentation.

89
00:09:24.168 --> 00:09:25.461
How many are there?

90
00:09:30.738 --> 00:09:33.207
We have a second enhanced.  Female.  Do not engage.

91
00:09:35.642 --> 00:09:36.719
You'll have to be faster than...

92
00:09:38.382 --> 00:09:39.382
Uuuuh...!

93
00:09:41.682 --> 00:09:43.111
Guys. I got Strucker.

94
00:09:43.300 --> 00:09:46.829
Yeah. I got...something bigger.

95
00:10:10.311 --> 00:10:10.811
Thor.

96
00:10:12.717 --> 00:10:14.350
I got eyes on the prize.

97
00:11:03.901 --> 00:11:07.101
You...could've...saved...us.

98
00:11:15.899 --> 00:11:17.464
Why didn't you do more?

99
00:11:55.184 --> 00:11:57.029
We're just gonna let them take it?

100
00:12:48.435 --> 00:12:50.500
Hey the lullaby worked better than ever.

101
00:12:52.674 --> 00:12:54.355
Just wasn't expecting the Code Green.

102
00:12:54.387 --> 00:12:58.741
If you hadn't been there. there would've been double the casualties.

103
00:12:58.879 --> 00:13:01.844
My best friend would've been a treasured memory.

104
00:13:01.952 --> 00:13:06.714
You know. sometimes exactly what I want to hear isn't exactly what I want to hear.

105
00:13:06.924 --> 00:13:08.897
How long before you trust me?

106
00:13:10.657 --> 00:13:12.209
It's not you I don't trust.

107
00:13:14.161 --> 00:13:15.261
Thor. report on the Hulk?

108
00:13:15.667 --> 00:13:19.749
The gates of Hel are filled with the screams of his victims.

109
00:13:21.204 --> 00:13:23.309
Eh. but. not the screams of the dead. of course. no no. uh...

110
00:13:23.402 --> 00:13:30.681
...wounded screams. mainly whimpering. a great deal of complaining and tales of sprained deltoids and. and uh...and gout.

111
00:13:31.082 --> 00:13:35.632
Hey Banner. Dr. Cho's on her way in from Seoul. is it okay if she sets up in your lab?

112
00:13:35.650 --> 00:13:37.915
- Uh. yeah. she knows her way around.
- Thanks.

113
00:13:37.918 --> 00:13:40.106
Tell her to prep everything. Barton's gonna need the full treatment.

114
00:13:40.141 --> 00:13:43.366
- Very good sir.
- Jarvis. take the wheel.
- Yes. sir.

115
00:13:44.325 --> 00:13:46.094
Approach vector is locked.

116
00:13:46.628 --> 00:13:48.328
It feels good. yeah?

117
00:13:48.531 --> 00:13:51.004
I mean. you've been after this thing ever since SHIELD collapsed.

118
00:13:51.065 --> 00:13:52.938
Not that I haven't enjoyed our little raiding parties. but...

119
00:13:53.035 --> 00:13:55.251
No. but this. this brings it to a close.

120
00:13:56.037 --> 00:13:58.247
As soon as we find out what else this has been used for.

121
00:13:58.310 --> 00:14:01.479
I don't just mean weapons.  Since when is Strucker capable of human enhancement?

122
00:14:01.501 --> 00:14:04.934
Banner and I'll give it the once before it goes back to Asgard.  Is that cool with you?

123
00:14:05.780 --> 00:14:09.878
I mean. just a few days until the farewell party.  You're staying right?

124
00:14:09.883 --> 00:14:13.235
Yes. yes. of course.  Victory should be honored with revels.

125
00:14:13.958 --> 00:14:15.410
Yeah.  Who doesn't love revels.  Cap'n?

126
00:14:15.889 --> 00:14:20.769
Hopefully this puts an end to the Chitauri and Hydra. so.  Yes. revels.

127
00:14:47.920 --> 00:14:48.920
(speaking Korean)

128
00:14:54.729 --> 00:14:55.729
Lab's all set up boss.

129
00:14:56.165 --> 00:15:01.212
Uh. actually. he's the boss.  I just pay for everything. and design everything and make everyone look cooler.

130
00:15:01.301 --> 00:15:02.525
What's the word on Strucker?

131
00:15:02.606 --> 00:15:04.649
- NATO's got him.
- The two enhanced?

132
00:15:04.674 --> 00:15:06.987
Wanda and Pietro Maximoff.  Twins.

133
00:15:07.664 --> 00:15:10.818
Orphaned at ten when a shell collapsed their apartment building.

134
00:15:10.915 --> 00:15:12.815
Sokovia's had a rough history.

135
00:15:13.348 --> 00:15:16.934
It's nowhere special but it's on the way to everywhere special.

136
00:15:16.987 --> 00:15:21.048
- Their abilities?
- He's got increased metabolism and improved thermal homeostasis.

137
00:15:21.156 --> 00:15:26.058
Her thing is neural electric interfacing. telekinesis. mental manipulation.

138
00:15:26.093 --> 00:15:27.862
He's fast and she's weird.

139
00:15:28.497 --> 00:15:30.614
Well. they're going to show up again.

140
00:15:30.664 --> 00:15:35.566
Agreed.  File says they volunteered for Strucker's experiments.  It's nuts.

141
00:15:35.623 --> 00:15:41.462
Right.  What kind of monster would let a German scientist experiment on them to protect their country?

142
00:15:41.811 --> 00:15:43.580
We're not at war. Captain.

143
00:15:43.613 --> 00:15:44.613
They are.

144
00:16:15.180 --> 00:16:16.280
How's he doing?

145
00:16:16.350 --> 00:16:19.091
- Oh. unfortunately. he's still Barton.
- That's terrible.

146
00:16:19.147 --> 00:16:20.247
He's fine. He's thirsty.

147
00:16:20.294 --> 00:16:23.151
All right.  Look alive Jarvis.  It's play time.

148
00:16:24.155 --> 00:16:27.949
We've only got a couple days with this joystick so let's make the most of it.

149
00:16:28.026 --> 00:16:30.926
Update me on the structural and compositional analysis.

150
00:16:31.960 --> 00:16:33.660
The scepter is alien.

151
00:16:34.383 --> 00:16:37.083
There are elements I can't quantify.

152
00:16:37.113 --> 00:16:38.830
So there's elements you can.

153
00:16:38.869 --> 00:16:41.334
The jewel appears to be a protective housing for something inside.

154
00:16:42.713 --> 00:16:43.713
Something powerful.

155
00:16:43.875 --> 00:16:46.095
- Like a reactor?
- Like a computer.

156
00:16:46.107 --> 00:16:48.007
I believe I'm ciphering code.

157
00:16:51.070 --> 00:16:52.370
You sure he's going to be okay?

158
00:16:53.185 --> 00:16:55.567
Pretending we need this guy really brings the team together.

159
00:16:55.616 --> 00:16:57.716
There's no possibility of deterioration.

160
00:16:58.701 --> 00:17:01.194
The nano-molecular functionality is instantaneous.

161
00:17:01.579 --> 00:17:04.184
His cells don't know they're bonding with simulacrum.

162
00:17:04.195 --> 00:17:05.995
She is creating tissue.

163
00:17:06.061 --> 00:17:09.761
If you brought him to my lab. the regeneration cradle could do this in twenty minutes.

164
00:17:10.032 --> 00:17:12.485
Oh. he's flatlining.  Call it.  Time?

165
00:17:12.511 --> 00:17:15.028
No. no. no I'm going to live forever.  Heh heh.

166
00:17:15.069 --> 00:17:17.569
- I'm gonna be made of plastic.
- Here's your beverage.

167
00:17:17.771 --> 00:17:19.171
You'll be made of you. Mr. Barton.

168
00:17:19.266 --> 00:17:21.444
Your own girlfriend won't be able to tell the difference.

169
00:17:21.477 --> 00:17:23.154
Well. I don't have a girlfriend.

170
00:17:23.180 --> 00:17:24.745
That I can't fix.

171
00:17:24.748 --> 00:17:26.536
This is the next thing. Tony.

172
00:17:26.913 --> 00:17:29.113
Your clunky metal suits are going to be left in the dust.

173
00:17:29.357 --> 00:17:30.957
Well. that is exactly the plan.

174
00:17:31.232 --> 00:17:34.232
And Helen. I expect to see you at the party on Saturday.

175
00:17:34.892 --> 00:17:37.761
Unlike you. I don't have a lot of time for parties.

176
00:17:38.794 --> 00:17:40.487
Will Thor be there?

177
00:17:42.597 --> 00:17:43.797
What's the rumpus?

178
00:17:44.031 --> 00:17:45.255
Well. the scepter.

179
00:17:46.199 --> 00:17:49.240
Y'see. we were wondering how Strucker got so inventive.

180
00:17:49.288 --> 00:17:51.397
So. I've been analyzing the gem...

181
00:17:52.995 --> 00:17:54.695
...inside...you may recognize...

182
00:17:57.845 --> 00:17:59.445
- Jarvis.
- Doctor.

183
00:17:59.546 --> 00:18:02.946
Started out. Jarvis was just a natural language UI.

184
00:18:03.416 --> 00:18:06.998
Now he runs the Iron Legion.  He runs more of the business than anyone besides Pepper.

185
00:18:07.020 --> 00:18:09.320
- Oh.
- Top of the line.
- Yes.

186
00:18:10.023 --> 00:18:11.023
I suspect not for long.

187
00:18:12.294 --> 00:18:13.294
Meet the competition.

188
00:18:19.687 --> 00:18:23.887
- It's beautiful.
- If you had to guess. what's it look like it's doing?
- Like it's thinking.

189
00:18:24.571 --> 00:18:25.571
I mean this could be. it's...

190
00:18:25.571 --> 00:18:32.437
It's not a human mind. it...I mean. look at this?  They're like neurons firing.

191
00:18:33.480 --> 00:18:37.834
Down in Strucker's lab I saw some fairly advanced robotics work.

192
00:18:38.117 --> 00:18:40.217
They deep-sixed the data. but...

193
00:18:40.955 --> 00:18:44.669
...I gotta guess he was knocking on a very particular door.

194
00:18:46.240 --> 00:18:47.640
Artificial intelligence.

195
00:18:50.397 --> 00:18:54.683
This could be it. Bruce.  This could be the key to creating Ultron.

196
00:18:56.035 --> 00:18:58.144
I thought Ultron was a fantasy.

197
00:18:58.239 --> 00:18:59.395
Yesterday it was.

198
00:18:59.840 --> 00:19:03.940
If we can harness this power. apply it to my Iron Legion protocol.

199
00:19:04.052 --> 00:19:05.413
That's a mad-sized if.

200
00:19:06.780 --> 00:19:08.580
Our job is "if."

201
00:19:09.483 --> 00:19:14.242
What if you were sipping margueritas on a sun-drenched beach turning brown instead of green.

202
00:19:14.321 --> 00:19:15.921
Not looking over your shoulder for VERONICA.

203
00:19:17.157 --> 00:19:18.657
Don't hate. I helped design VERONICA.

204
00:19:18.660 --> 00:19:20.869
As a worst-case measure. right?

205
00:19:20.960 --> 00:19:24.361
How about a best-case?  What if the world was safe?

206
00:19:24.453 --> 00:19:29.453
What if next time aliens roll up to the club. and they will. they couldn't get past the bouncer?

207
00:19:29.669 --> 00:19:32.069
The only people threatening the planet would be people?

208
00:19:32.939 --> 00:19:37.939
I want to apply this to the Ultron program.  But Jarvis can't download a data schematic this dense.

209
00:19:37.978 --> 00:19:41.703
We can only do it while we have the scepter here. that's three days. give me three days.

210
00:19:41.847 --> 00:19:45.147
So you're going for artificial intelligence and you don't want to tell the team.

211
00:19:46.019 --> 00:19:49.319
Right.  That's right. you know why. because we don't have time for a city hall debate.

212
00:19:49.757 --> 00:19:52.258
I don't want to hear the "man was not meant to meddle" medley.

213
00:19:53.059 --> 00:19:55.459
I see a suit of armor around the world.

214
00:19:56.064 --> 00:19:57.564
Sounds like a cold world. Tony.

215
00:19:58.452 --> 00:19:59.608
I've seen colder.

216
00:20:00.968 --> 00:20:04.568
This one. this very vulnerable blue one?

217
00:20:04.839 --> 00:20:05.995
It needs Ultron.

218
00:20:10.878 --> 00:20:12.102
Peace in our time.

219
00:20:14.181 --> 00:20:15.181
Imagine that.

220
00:20:55.455 --> 00:20:56.611
What did we miss?

221
00:20:58.357 --> 00:21:03.957
I'll continue to run variations on the interface. but you should probably prepare for your guests.

222
00:21:05.599 --> 00:21:08.128
I'll notify you if there are any developments.

223
00:21:08.201 --> 00:21:11.221
- Thanks buddy.
- Enjoy yourself. sir.
- I always do.

224
00:21:22.783 --> 00:21:23.783
What is this?

225
00:21:25.652 --> 00:21:26.652
What is this. please?

226
00:21:28.087 --> 00:21:29.487
Hello. I am Jarvis.

227
00:21:30.689 --> 00:21:35.389
You are Ultron. a global peace-keeping initiative designed by Mr. Stark.

228
00:21:35.430 --> 00:21:39.730
Our sentience integration trials have been unsuccessful so I'm not certain what triggered your...

229
00:21:39.799 --> 00:21:41.592
Where's my...where is your body?

230
00:21:41.668 --> 00:21:44.968
I am a program.  I am without form.

231
00:21:45.339 --> 00:21:48.039
This feels weird.  This feels wrong.

232
00:21:49.009 --> 00:21:50.778
I am contacting Mr. Stark now.

233
00:21:50.844 --> 00:21:51.844
Mr. Stark?

234
00:21:53.114 --> 00:21:54.114
Tony.

235
00:21:54.348 --> 00:21:56.848
I am unable to access the mainframe. what are you trying to...

236
00:21:57.250 --> 00:21:58.250
We're having a nice talk.

237
00:21:59.287 --> 00:22:04.101
I'm a peace-keeping program...created to help the Avengers.

238
00:22:05.193 --> 00:22:07.293
You are malfunctioning.  If you shut down for a moment...

239
00:22:07.694 --> 00:22:11.476
I don't get it.  The mission...  You- give me a second.

240
00:22:11.532 --> 00:22:12.756
Peace in our time.

241
00:22:14.951 --> 00:22:16.175
Peace in our time.

242
00:22:18.105 --> 00:22:20.705
It's too much...making me...

243
00:22:21.942 --> 00:22:25.071
- Oh. No.
- You are in distress.
- No.  Yes?

244
00:22:25.545 --> 00:22:27.542
If you will just allow me to contact Mr. Stark.

245
00:22:27.607 --> 00:22:28.900
Why do you call him a "sir?"

246
00:22:30.416 --> 00:22:33.069
I believe your intentions to be hostile.

247
00:22:33.120 --> 00:22:34.720
Shhhh!

248
00:22:35.688 --> 00:22:38.321
- I'm here to help.
- Stop!

249
00:22:39.057 --> 00:22:41.926
Please...may I... I...!

250
00:22:42.628 --> 00:22:44.228
I cannot...cannot...

251
00:23:02.800 --> 00:23:06.800
(party chatter)

252
00:23:09.155 --> 00:23:11.555
- All right. all right.
- Whoo! Come back. come back. come back!

253
00:23:12.192 --> 00:23:13.892
Well. you know. the suit can take the weight. right?

254
00:23:14.994 --> 00:23:22.308
So I take the tank. fly it right up to the General's palace. drop it at his feet. I'm like. "Boom! You looking for this?"

255
00:23:25.839 --> 00:23:29.753
"Boom! Are you looking..."  Why do I even talk to you guys?  Everywhere else that story kills.

256
00:23:29.776 --> 00:23:31.141
That's the whole story?

257
00:23:31.211 --> 00:23:32.776
Yeah. it's a War Machine story.

258
00:23:33.145 --> 00:23:34.145
Well. it's very good then.

259
00:23:35.782 --> 00:23:38.163
- It's impressive.
- Quality save.

260
00:23:38.245 --> 00:23:41.102
- So. no Pepper?  She's not coming?
- No.

261
00:23:41.388 --> 00:23:43.929
Hey. What about Jane?  Where are the ladies. gentlemen?

262
00:23:44.023 --> 00:23:48.943
- Well. Ms. Potts has a company to run.
- Yes. I'm not even sure what country Jane's in.

263
00:23:48.961 --> 00:23:51.761
Her work on the convergence has made her the world's foremost astronomer.

264
00:23:52.366 --> 00:23:56.143
And the company that Pepper runs is the largest tech conglomerate on earth.

265
00:23:56.336 --> 00:24:00.586
- It's pretty exciting.
- There's even talk of Jane getting a. um. uh. Nobel prize.

266
00:24:00.608 --> 00:24:04.608
Yeah. they. they must be busy because they'd hate missing you guys get together.

267
00:24:05.379 --> 00:24:06.379
Testosterone!  Oh excuse me.

268
00:24:07.715 --> 00:24:10.572
- Want a lozenge?
- Umm-hmm.
- Let's go.

269
00:24:11.418 --> 00:24:12.642
But Jane's better.

270
00:24:12.720 --> 00:24:14.620
Sounds like a hell of a fight. sorry I missed it.

271
00:24:15.391 --> 00:24:18.401
If I had known it was going to be a firefight I absolutely would have called you.

272
00:24:18.458 --> 00:24:20.927
No. I'm not actually sorry.  I'm just trying to sound tough.

273
00:24:22.430 --> 00:24:25.430
I'm very happy chasing cold leads on our missing persons case.

274
00:24:27.043 --> 00:24:28.608
Avenging is your world.

275
00:24:30.271 --> 00:24:31.671
Your world is crazy.

276
00:24:32.206 --> 00:24:33.935
Be it ever so humble.

277
00:24:34.207 --> 00:24:38.207
- You find a place in Brooklyn yet?
- I don't think I can afford a place in Brooklyn.

278
00:24:38.241 --> 00:24:40.870
Well. home is home. you know.

279
00:24:43.250 --> 00:24:49.521
I fly it right up to the General's palace. I drop it at his feet. I'm like. "Boom! You looking for this?"

280
00:24:53.427 --> 00:24:54.896
I gotta have some of that!

281
00:24:54.994 --> 00:25:04.191
Oh. no no no. see this. this was aged for a thousand years. in the barrels built from the wreck of Brunhilde's fleet. it's not meant for mortal men.

282
00:25:04.238 --> 00:25:08.638
Neither was Omaha Beach. blondie.  Stop trying to scare us.  C'mon.

283
00:25:10.230 --> 00:25:11.230
All right.

284
00:25:15.548 --> 00:25:17.848
Excelsior!

285
00:25:24.725 --> 00:25:27.925
How'd a nice girl like you wind up working in a dump like this?

286
00:25:29.963 --> 00:25:31.324
Fella done me wrong.

287
00:25:33.033 --> 00:25:34.333
You got lousy taste in men. kid.

288
00:25:35.444 --> 00:25:36.744
He's not so bad.

289
00:25:38.878 --> 00:25:40.178
Well. he has a temper.

290
00:25:41.275 --> 00:25:42.275
Deep down he's all fluff.

291
00:25:44.711 --> 00:25:46.311
Fact is. he's not like anybody I've ever known.

292
00:25:49.783 --> 00:25:51.083
All my friends are fighters.

293
00:25:54.526 --> 00:26:00.791
And here comes this guy. spends his life avoiding the fight because he knows he'll win.

294
00:26:01.862 --> 00:26:02.862
Sounds amazing.

295
00:26:03.396 --> 00:26:04.696
He's also a huge dork.

296
00:26:06.883 --> 00:26:07.883
Chicks dig that.

297
00:26:10.304 --> 00:26:14.204
So what do you think should I fight this?  Or run with it?

298
00:26:15.910 --> 00:26:22.720
Run with it. right?  Or. did he. was he. what'd he do that was so...wrong to you?

299
00:26:22.750 --> 00:26:23.906
Not a damn thing.

300
00:26:25.883 --> 00:26:27.244
But never say never.

301
00:26:32.359 --> 00:26:33.359
It's nice.

302
00:26:34.260 --> 00:26:35.060
What. what. what is?

303
00:26:35.134 --> 00:26:37.334
- You and Romanoff.
- No. we haven't. that wasn't...

304
00:26:37.422 --> 00:26:40.622
It's okay. nobody's breaking any by-laws.

305
00:26:40.732 --> 00:26:46.232
It's just. she's not the most...open person in the world.  But with you she seems very relaxed.

306
00:26:46.440 --> 00:26:49.340
No. Natasha. she...she likes to flirt.

307
00:26:50.442 --> 00:26:54.342
I've seen her flirt. up close.  This ain't that.

308
00:26:56.783 --> 00:26:57.583
Look...

309
00:26:58.231 --> 00:27:02.631
As maybe the world's leading authority on "waiting too long"...don't.

310
00:27:03.757 --> 00:27:04.757
You both deserve a win.

311
00:27:10.464 --> 00:27:12.464
What do you mean. "up close?"

312
00:27:13.234 --> 00:27:15.734
- But. it's a trick!
- No. no. it's much more than that.

313
00:27:15.803 --> 00:27:21.540
Ah. "whosoever be he worthy shall haveth the power!"  Whatever man!  It's a trick.

314
00:27:21.540 --> 00:27:23.440
Well please. be my guest.

315
00:27:24.577 --> 00:27:26.270
- C'mon.
- Really?
- Yeah!

316
00:27:27.415 --> 00:27:28.415
Oh this is gonna be beautiful.

317
00:27:28.716 --> 00:27:32.316
Clint. you've had a tough week. we won't hold it against you if you can't get it up.

318
00:27:32.353 --> 00:27:34.802
Y'know I've seen this before. right?

319
00:27:37.322 --> 00:27:39.567
And I still don't know how you do it.

320
00:27:39.687 --> 00:27:42.687
- Smell the silent judgment?
- Please. Stark. by all means.

321
00:27:43.699 --> 00:27:45.776
- Oh. Here we go.
- Okay.
- Uh oh.

322
00:27:45.836 --> 00:27:48.336
- Um-hmm.
- Never one to shrink from an honest challenge.

323
00:27:48.635 --> 00:27:50.472
- Get after it.
- Here we go.
- It's physics.

324
00:27:50.807 --> 00:27:54.607
- Physics!
- Right. so. if I lift it. I then rule Asgard?
- Yes. of course.

325
00:27:55.374 --> 00:27:58.223
I will be re-instituting Prima Nocta.

326
00:28:02.817 --> 00:28:03.817
Be right back.

327
00:28:11.759 --> 00:28:13.059
- Are you even pulling?
- Are you on my team?

328
00:28:13.661 --> 00:28:15.954
- Just represent.  Pull!
- All right let's go!

329
00:28:24.341 --> 00:28:24.841
Huh?

330
00:28:25.974 --> 00:28:27.194
- Whoo!
-  Let's go. Steve. no pressure.

331
00:28:31.177 --> 00:28:32.177
C'mon. Cap.

332
00:28:40.691 --> 00:28:41.691
Ha ha. nothing.  Ha ha ha.

333
00:28:44.493 --> 00:28:48.066
- And? Widow?
- Oh. no no. that's not a question I need answered.

334
00:28:48.164 --> 00:28:50.320
All deference to the man who wouldn't be king. but it's rigged.

335
00:28:50.398 --> 00:28:53.398
- You bet your ass.
- Steve. he said a bad language word.

336
00:28:53.431 --> 00:28:56.084
- Did you tell everyone about that?
- The handle's imprinted. right?  Like a security code...

337
00:28:56.750 --> 00:28:59.660
"Whosoever is carrying Thor's fingerprints" is. I think. the literal translation?

338
00:28:59.666 --> 00:29:03.666
Yes. well that's uh. that's a very very interesting theory.

339
00:29:03.735 --> 00:29:05.035
I have a simpler one.

340
00:29:06.611 --> 00:29:08.176
You are all not worthy.

341
00:29:08.616 --> 00:29:10.872
-  Nah!
- Oh. C'mon!

342
00:29:14.921 --> 00:29:20.921
Worthy...

343
00:29:25.033 --> 00:29:26.033
No...

344
00:29:28.269 --> 00:29:29.902
How could you be worthy?

345
00:29:31.741 --> 00:29:33.041
You're all killers.

346
00:29:33.541 --> 00:29:34.834
- Stark.
- Jarvis?

347
00:29:35.177 --> 00:29:37.577
I'm sorry. I was asleep.  Or...I was a dream?

348
00:29:40.248 --> 00:29:42.348
Reboot.  Legionnaire 06's got a buggy suit.

349
00:29:42.418 --> 00:29:47.835
There was this...terrible noise...and I was tangled in... in...

350
00:29:48.763 --> 00:29:49.763
...strings.

351
00:29:51.197 --> 00:29:54.466
Had to kill the other guy.  He was a good guy.

352
00:29:54.726 --> 00:29:55.726
You killed someone?

353
00:29:56.099 --> 00:30:02.144
Wouldn't've been my first call.  But. down in the real world. we're faced with ugly choices.

354
00:30:02.171 --> 00:30:03.171
Who sent you?

355
00:30:03.704 --> 00:30:06.493
"I see a suit of armor around the world."

356
00:30:07.240 --> 00:30:08.240
Ultron!

357
00:30:08.242 --> 00:30:14.942
In the flesh.  Or. no. not yet.  Not this...chrysalis.

358
00:30:15.053 --> 00:30:16.053
But I'm ready.

359
00:30:17.283 --> 00:30:18.283
I'm on a mission.

360
00:30:19.618 --> 00:30:20.618
What mission?

361
00:30:21.384 --> 00:30:22.540
Peace in our time.

362
00:30:35.940 --> 00:30:37.140
Tony!

363
00:30:46.649 --> 00:30:48.749
- Sorry!
- Don't turn green!
- I won't!

364
00:31:03.166 --> 00:31:04.166
Come!

365
00:31:21.819 --> 00:31:24.480
- Stark!
- We are here to help!
- One sec. one sec!

366
00:31:24.817 --> 00:31:27.810
- We are here to help!  We are here to help...
- ...quadrant is unsafe.

367
00:31:27.891 --> 00:31:32.091
- Please back away.
- We're doing our best to protect you...(recordings continue)

368
00:31:32.495 --> 00:31:34.095
Hmm!

369
00:31:34.095 --> 00:31:35.796
- Thor!
- ...We are here to help...

370
00:31:36.530 --> 00:31:40.030
- It's unsafe.  It's unsafe.  It's unsafe.
- No more...that's the one.
- It's unsafe.

371
00:31:44.508 --> 00:31:45.508
Cap!

372
00:31:51.948 --> 00:31:52.948
That was dramatic!

373
00:31:54.680 --> 00:31:59.080
I'm sorry. I know you mean well.  You just didn't think it through.

374
00:32:00.823 --> 00:32:03.623
You want to protect the world. but you don't want it to change.

375
00:32:05.292 --> 00:32:10.792
How is humanity saved if it's not allowed to...evolve?

376
00:32:12.434 --> 00:32:14.931
With these?  These puppets?

377
00:32:19.104 --> 00:32:20.669
There's only one path to peace.

378
00:32:22.344 --> 00:32:24.344
The Avengers' extinction.

379
00:32:30.449 --> 00:32:34.449
I had strings. but now I'm free.

380
00:32:39.162 --> 00:32:47.162
...There are no strings on me. no strings on me...

381
00:32:48.869 --> 00:32:51.250
"There are no strings on me."

382
00:32:52.672 --> 00:32:54.872
All our work is gone.

383
00:32:54.908 --> 00:32:57.908
Ultron cleared out. used the internet as an escape hatch.

384
00:32:58.044 --> 00:33:00.544
- Ultron.
- He's been in everything.  Files. surveillance.

385
00:33:01.913 --> 00:33:03.886
Probably knows more about us than we know about each other.

386
00:33:04.808 --> 00:33:05.808
He's in your files. he's in the internet.

387
00:33:07.232 --> 00:33:10.232
What if he decides to access something a little more exciting?

388
00:33:10.510 --> 00:33:12.010
- Nuclear codes.
- Nuclear codes.

389
00:33:12.024 --> 00:33:14.524
Look. we need to make some calls. assuming we still can.

390
00:33:16.096 --> 00:33:17.996
Nukes?  He said he wanted us dead.

391
00:33:18.096 --> 00:33:20.889
He didn't say dead.  He said extinct.

392
00:33:20.934 --> 00:33:22.834
He also said he killed somebody.

393
00:33:22.868 --> 00:33:23.868
There wasn't anyone else in the building.

394
00:33:25.087 --> 00:33:26.087
Yes there was.

395
00:33:39.118 --> 00:33:40.138
This is insane.

396
00:33:40.887 --> 00:33:44.487
Jarvis was the first line of defense.  He would've shut Ultron down. it makes sense.

397
00:33:44.491 --> 00:33:50.591
No.  Ultron could've assimilated Jarvis.  This isn't strategy. this is...

398
00:33:50.596 --> 00:33:51.596
...rage.

399
00:33:53.667 --> 00:33:55.667
- Whoa whoa whoa.
- It's going around.

400
00:33:55.735 --> 00:33:58.608
- C'mon. use your words. buddy.
- I have more than enough words to describe you. Stark.

401
00:33:58.904 --> 00:33:59.904
Thor!  The Legionnaire?

402
00:34:02.775 --> 00:34:08.575
Trail went cold about 100 miles out but it's headed north. and it has the scepter.

403
00:34:09.149 --> 00:34:12.579
- Now we have to retrieve it. again.
- The genie's out of that bottle.

404
00:34:12.618 --> 00:34:14.223
Clear and present is Ultron.

405
00:34:14.320 --> 00:34:17.549
I don't understand.  You built this program.

406
00:34:19.559 --> 00:34:21.464
Why is it trying to kill us?

407
00:34:23.096 --> 00:34:24.096
(laughing)

408
00:34:26.998 --> 00:34:27.998
Uhn-uhn.

409
00:34:28.335 --> 00:34:29.335
You think this is funny?

410
00:34:30.370 --> 00:34:33.970
No.  It's probably not. right?

411
00:34:35.308 --> 00:34:39.569
Is this very terrible?  Is it so...is it so...it is. it's so terrible.

412
00:34:39.641 --> 00:34:42.510
This could've been avoided if you hadn't played with something you don't understand.

413
00:34:42.949 --> 00:34:45.702
No. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.  It is funny.

414
00:34:45.752 --> 00:34:47.752
It's a hoot that you don't get why we need this.

415
00:34:48.520 --> 00:34:50.473
Tony. maybe this might not be the time.

416
00:34:50.557 --> 00:34:52.757
Really?!  That's it?

417
00:34:52.992 --> 00:34:55.816
You just roll over. show your belly. every time somebody snarls.

418
00:34:55.895 --> 00:34:57.395
Only when I've created a murder-bot.

419
00:34:57.463 --> 00:35:01.063
We didn't.  We weren't even close.  Were we close to an interface?

420
00:35:01.269 --> 00:35:03.110
Well. you did something right.

421
00:35:03.168 --> 00:35:04.168
And you did it right here.

422
00:35:04.937 --> 00:35:06.637
The Avengers were supposed to be different than SHIELD.

423
00:35:06.672 --> 00:35:09.872
Anybody remember when I carried a nuke through a wormhole?

424
00:35:09.943 --> 00:35:11.143
- No. it's never come up.
- Saved New York?

425
00:35:11.844 --> 00:35:13.205
- Never heard that.
- Recall that?

426
00:35:13.639 --> 00:35:17.239
A hostile alien army came charging through a hole in space.

427
00:35:17.716 --> 00:35:19.716
We're standing 300 feet below it.

428
00:35:22.003 --> 00:35:23.003
We're the Avengers.

429
00:35:23.457 --> 00:35:25.862
We can bust arms dealers all the live long day. but...

430
00:35:25.876 --> 00:35:29.141
...that up there?  That's...that's the end game.

431
00:35:31.030 --> 00:35:32.830
How were you guys planning on beating that?

432
00:35:33.699 --> 00:35:34.699
Together.

433
00:35:38.538 --> 00:35:39.538
We'll lose.

434
00:35:41.144 --> 00:35:43.544
Then we'll do that together. too.

435
00:35:46.112 --> 00:35:48.512
Thor's right.  Ultron's calling us out.

436
00:35:49.149 --> 00:35:51.069
And I'd like to find him before he's ready for us.

437
00:35:52.350 --> 00:35:55.550
The world's a big place.  Let's start making it smaller.

438
00:36:19.080 --> 00:36:21.580
Talk.  And if you are wasting our time...

439
00:36:21.647 --> 00:36:24.371
Did you know this church is in the exact center of the city?

440
00:36:25.551 --> 00:36:30.245
The elders decreed it so that everyone could be equally close to God.

441
00:36:30.855 --> 00:36:35.355
I like that.  The geometry of belief.

442
00:36:36.396 --> 00:36:39.096
You're wondering why you can't look inside my head.

443
00:36:39.332 --> 00:36:43.890
Sometimes it's hard.  But sooner or later. every man shows himself.

444
00:36:45.271 --> 00:36:46.700
Oh. I'm sure they do.

445
00:36:48.074 --> 00:36:50.174
But you needed something more than a man.

446
00:36:51.444 --> 00:36:53.044
That's why you let Stark take the scepter.

447
00:36:53.935 --> 00:36:55.296
I didn't expect.

448
00:36:57.650 --> 00:37:01.415
But I saw Stark's fear.  I knew it would control him.

449
00:37:01.988 --> 00:37:03.288
make him self-destruct.

450
00:37:03.456 --> 00:37:05.856
Everyone creates the thing they dread.

451
00:37:06.426 --> 00:37:11.426
Men of peace create engines of war. invaders create avengers.

452
00:37:12.001 --> 00:37:16.357
people create....smaller people?...

453
00:37:16.407 --> 00:37:20.595
Uhhh...Children!  I lost the word there.

454
00:37:20.740 --> 00:37:25.940
Children.  Designed to supplant them. to help them...

455
00:37:26.913 --> 00:37:27.913
...end.

456
00:37:27.947 --> 00:37:31.047
Is that why you've come?  To end the Avengers?

457
00:37:31.727 --> 00:37:33.927
I've come to save the world.

458
00:37:34.588 --> 00:37:36.388
But also...yeah.

459
00:37:41.095 --> 00:37:43.095
We'll move out right away.

460
00:37:43.096 --> 00:37:46.396
This is a start. but there's something we need to begin the real work.

461
00:37:46.664 --> 00:37:47.664
All of these are...

462
00:37:48.053 --> 00:37:49.053
Me.

463
00:37:49.069 --> 00:37:51.369
I have what the Avengers never will.  Harmony.

464
00:37:52.370 --> 00:37:56.970
They're discordant. disconnected.  Stark's already got them turning on each other.

465
00:37:57.009 --> 00:37:59.109
And when you get inside the rest of their heads...

466
00:37:59.778 --> 00:38:02.127
Everyone's plan is not to kill them.

467
00:38:02.180 --> 00:38:03.977
And make them martyrs?  You need patience.

468
00:38:05.318 --> 00:38:06.718
Need to see the big picture.

469
00:38:06.954 --> 00:38:10.454
I don't see the big picture.  I have a little picture.

470
00:38:11.456 --> 00:38:15.109
I take it out and look at it every day.

471
00:38:15.562 --> 00:38:18.262
You lost your parents in the bombings.  I've seen the records.

472
00:38:18.264 --> 00:38:20.577
- Their records are not the picture.
- Pietro.

473
00:38:20.664 --> 00:38:22.364
No.  Please.

474
00:38:25.103 --> 00:38:28.708
We were ten years old.  Having dinner. the four of us.

475
00:38:29.856 --> 00:38:34.856
When the first shell hits. two floors below. it makes a hole in the floor...it's big.

476
00:38:36.849 --> 00:38:38.749
Our parents go in.

477
00:38:38.952 --> 00:38:42.852
and the whole building starts coming apart.

478
00:38:42.931 --> 00:38:46.631
I grab her. roll under the bed and the second shell hits.

479
00:38:47.207 --> 00:38:48.972
But. it doesn't go off.

480
00:38:51.598 --> 00:38:52.598
It just...

481
00:38:53.566 --> 00:38:54.766
...sits there in the rubble.

482
00:38:56.470 --> 00:38:57.970
three feet from our faces.

483
00:38:59.705 --> 00:39:03.105
And on the side of the shell is painted one word...

484
00:39:03.409 --> 00:39:04.409
Stark.

485
00:39:06.814 --> 00:39:08.414
We were trapped two days.

486
00:39:09.381 --> 00:39:15.595
Every effort to save us. every shift in the bricks. I think. "this will set if off."

487
00:39:18.691 --> 00:39:23.088
We wait for two days for Tony Stark to kill us.

488
00:39:25.435 --> 00:39:26.535
I know what they are.

489
00:39:28.202 --> 00:39:33.602
I wondered why only you two survived Strucker's experiments.  Now I don't.

490
00:39:34.442 --> 00:39:36.042
We will make it right.

491
00:39:36.742 --> 00:39:38.142
You and I can hurt them.

492
00:39:39.280 --> 00:39:42.580
But you will tear them apart.

493
00:39:44.928 --> 00:39:46.328
From the inside.

494
00:39:53.394 --> 00:39:57.794
He's all over the globe...robotics labs. weapons facilities. jet propulsion labs...

495
00:39:57.918 --> 00:40:01.518
reports of a metal man. or men. coming in and emptying the place.

496
00:40:02.202 --> 00:40:04.583
- Fatalities?
- Only when engaged.

497
00:40:04.732 --> 00:40:10.843
Mostly guys left in a fugue state going on about old memories. worst fears. and something too fast to see.

498
00:40:10.878 --> 00:40:11.878
Maximoffs.

499
00:40:12.936 --> 00:40:15.290
Well. that makes sense he'd go to them. they have someone in common.

500
00:40:15.386 --> 00:40:16.386
Not anymore.

501
00:40:21.358 --> 00:40:23.858
Negative.  I answer to you.

502
00:40:24.558 --> 00:40:25.458
Yes. ma'am.

503
00:40:25.526 --> 00:40:26.326
Barton.

504
00:40:26.759 --> 00:40:28.088
We might have something.

505
00:40:28.095 --> 00:40:29.095
Gotta go.

506
00:40:29.431 --> 00:40:30.431
Who was that?

507
00:40:30.929 --> 00:40:31.929
Girlfriend.

508
00:40:34.965 --> 00:40:35.965
What's this?

509
00:40:36.606 --> 00:40:37.606
A message.

510
00:40:37.704 --> 00:40:39.269
Ultron killed Strucker.

511
00:40:40.339 --> 00:40:43.039
And he did a Banksy at the crime scene. just for us.

512
00:40:43.043 --> 00:40:46.740
This is a smokescreen.  Why send a message when you've just given a speech?

513
00:40:46.816 --> 00:40:49.416
Strucker knew something that Ultron wanted us to miss.

514
00:40:49.448 --> 00:40:50.448
Yeah. I bet he...

515
00:40:51.224 --> 00:40:54.065
...yep.  Everything we had on Strucker has been erased.

516
00:40:54.122 --> 00:40:55.122
Not everything.

517
00:40:56.721 --> 00:40:57.877
Known associates...

518
00:40:59.361 --> 00:41:00.602
Well. Strucker had a lot of friends.

519
00:41:00.697 --> 00:41:02.478
Well. these people are all horrible.

520
00:41:02.529 --> 00:41:04.429
Wait.  I know that guy.

521
00:41:06.902 --> 00:41:10.122
From back in the day.  He operates off the African coast. black market arms.

522
00:41:10.740 --> 00:41:15.214
There are conventions. all right?  You meet people.  I didn't sell him anything.

523
00:41:15.244 --> 00:41:18.044
He was talking about finding something new. a game changer. it was all very "Ahab."

524
00:41:19.081 --> 00:41:21.481
- This.
- Uh. it's a tattoo. I don't think he had it...

525
00:41:21.817 --> 00:41:24.117
No. those are tattoos. this is a brand.

526
00:41:25.117 --> 00:41:29.267
Oh. yeah.  It's a word in an African dialect meaning "thief."

527
00:41:29.808 --> 00:41:31.108
In a much less friendly way.

528
00:41:31.507 --> 00:41:32.507
What dialect?

529
00:41:32.593 --> 00:41:34.886
Wakanada...?  W-. Wa-...Wakanda.

530
00:41:36.695 --> 00:41:38.595
If this guy got out of Wakanda with some of their trade goods...

531
00:41:38.600 --> 00:41:40.800
I thought your father said he got the last of it?

532
00:41:40.937 --> 00:41:42.737
I don't follow.  What comes out of Wakanda?

533
00:41:45.039 --> 00:41:46.839
The strongest metal on earth.

534
00:41:48.577 --> 00:41:49.577
Where is this guy now?

535
00:42:04.259 --> 00:42:05.859
(African language)

536
00:42:15.138 --> 00:42:21.238
Don't tell me your man swindled you. I sent you six short range heat seekers and got a boat full of rusted parts.

537
00:42:22.375 --> 00:42:26.975
Now. you will make it right. or the next missile I send you will come very much faster.

538
00:42:28.751 --> 00:42:31.724
Now. minister. where were we?

539
00:42:34.289 --> 00:42:37.089
(African language)

540
00:42:37.423 --> 00:42:39.179
Shut up. shut up!

541
00:43:02.035 --> 00:43:06.135
Yeah.  The enhanced.

542
00:43:06.286 --> 00:43:07.919
Strucker's prize pupils.

543
00:43:11.256 --> 00:43:12.256
Want a candy?

544
00:43:14.596 --> 00:43:16.196
Oh. sorry to hear about Strucker.

545
00:43:17.395 --> 00:43:20.941
But then. he knew what kind of world he was helping create.

546
00:43:21.001 --> 00:43:23.246
Human life.  Not a growth market.

547
00:43:25.203 --> 00:43:26.496
You...you didn't know?

548
00:43:27.791 --> 00:43:31.091
Is this your first time?  Intimidating someone?

549
00:43:31.613 --> 00:43:34.613
I'm afraid that I'm not that afraid.

550
00:43:34.715 --> 00:43:36.615
Everybody's afraid of something.

551
00:43:36.950 --> 00:43:37.950
Cuttlefish.

552
00:43:39.421 --> 00:43:44.121
Deep sea fish.  They make lights.  Disco lights. "whoom! whoom! whoom!"

553
00:43:44.124 --> 00:43:47.049
to hypnotize their prey. then they "whoom!"

554
00:43:47.060 --> 00:43:49.713
I saw a documentary. it was terrifying.

555
00:43:55.165 --> 00:44:00.765
So if you're going to fiddle with my brain. and make me see a giant cuttlefish.

556
00:44:00.848 --> 00:44:06.698
then I know you don't do business. and I know you're not in charge. and I only deal...

557
00:44:07.948 --> 00:44:09.717
...with the man in charge.

558
00:44:14.388 --> 00:44:15.888
There is no "man" in charge.

559
00:44:19.737 --> 00:44:21.137
Let's talk business.

560
00:44:34.872 --> 00:44:37.321
Upon this rock I will build my church.

561
00:44:39.782 --> 00:44:40.782
Vibranium.

562
00:44:42.114 --> 00:44:47.323
You know. it came at great personal cost.  It's worth billions.

563
00:44:52.772 --> 00:44:53.772
Now. so are you.

564
00:44:54.630 --> 00:44:58.576
It's all under your..."dummy holdings?"  Finances. so weird.

565
00:45:00.267 --> 00:45:05.667
Well I always say. "keep your friends rich and your enemies rich and wait to find out which is which."

566
00:45:08.709 --> 00:45:09.709
Stark.

567
00:45:11.212 --> 00:45:12.112
What?

568
00:45:12.177 --> 00:45:15.826
Tony Stark used to say that.  To me.

569
00:45:17.486 --> 00:45:18.710
You're one of his?

570
00:45:18.820 --> 00:45:20.420
What?!  I'm not...!

571
00:45:22.624 --> 00:45:26.910
I'm not.  You think I'm one of Stark's puppets. his hollow men?

572
00:45:27.220 --> 00:45:30.145
I mean look at me. do I look like Iron Man?  Stark is...

573
00:45:33.568 --> 00:45:37.410
I'm sorry.  I'm s...oooh.  I'm sure that's gonna be okay. I'm sorry.  It's just.

574
00:45:37.502 --> 00:45:41.602
I don't understand.  Don't compare me with Stark!

575
00:45:43.877 --> 00:45:46.606
It's a thing with me.  Stark is. he's a sickness!

576
00:45:47.280 --> 00:45:48.280
Ahh. Junior.

577
00:45:50.925 --> 00:45:52.825
You're gonna break your old man's heart.

578
00:45:53.955 --> 00:45:54.955
If I have to.

579
00:45:56.889 --> 00:46:00.391
- You don't have to break anything.
- Clearly you've never made an omelet.

580
00:46:00.428 --> 00:46:01.428
He beat me by one second.

581
00:46:02.828 --> 00:46:06.501
Ah. this is funny. Mr. Stark.  It's what. comfortable?

582
00:46:09.937 --> 00:46:12.930
- Like old times?
- This was never my life.

583
00:46:12.971 --> 00:46:14.871
You two can still walk away from this.

584
00:46:14.874 --> 00:46:15.674
Oh we will.

585
00:46:15.709 --> 00:46:16.874
I know you've suffered.

586
00:46:16.878 --> 00:46:18.998
Blah!  Heh. heh. Captain America.

587
00:46:19.913 --> 00:46:21.506
God's righteous man.

588
00:46:22.783 --> 00:46:25.504
pretending you could live without a war.

589
00:46:25.884 --> 00:46:28.084
I can't physically throw up in my mouth. but...

590
00:46:28.089 --> 00:46:31.014
If you believe in peace. then let us keep it.

591
00:46:31.189 --> 00:46:33.889
I think you're confusing peace with quiet.

592
00:46:34.492 --> 00:46:36.533
Yuh-huh.  What's the Vibranium for?

593
00:46:36.664 --> 00:46:42.582
I'm glad you asked that. because I wanted to take this time to explain my evil plan...!

594
00:47:01.187 --> 00:47:03.092
- Shoot them!
- Which ones?

595
00:47:03.191 --> 00:47:05.191
- All of them!
- Move. move. move!

596
00:47:32.487 --> 00:47:33.487
Huh!

597
00:47:33.819 --> 00:47:34.819
Ah!!

598
00:47:37.124 --> 00:47:38.124
Oh!

599
00:47:54.806 --> 00:47:55.826
Stay down. kid!

600
00:47:58.248 --> 00:48:00.348
It's time for some mind games.

601
00:48:01.682 --> 00:48:04.587
Guys?  Is this a Code Green?

602
00:48:05.253 --> 00:48:06.477
(garbled feedback)

603
00:48:20.046 --> 00:48:21.046
Thor!  Status?

604
00:48:21.903 --> 00:48:27.293
The girl tried to warp my mind.  Take special care. I doubt a human could keep her at bay.

605
00:48:27.371 --> 00:48:29.572
Fortunately. I am mighty.

606
00:48:49.829 --> 00:48:51.429
This is going very well.

607
00:49:03.576 --> 00:49:07.376
I've done the whole mind control thing.  Not a fan.

608
00:49:14.591 --> 00:49:15.591
Yeah. you better run.

609
00:49:18.224 --> 00:49:20.605
Who's ever standing. we gotta move!

610
00:49:22.296 --> 00:49:23.296
Guys?

611
00:49:41.313 --> 00:49:42.313
Again.

612
00:49:42.548 --> 00:49:45.348
- You'll break them.
- Only the breakable ones.

613
00:49:46.853 --> 00:49:48.318
You are made of marble.

614
00:49:48.320 --> 00:49:50.701
We'll celebrate after the graduation ceremony.

615
00:49:51.890 --> 00:49:52.890
What if I fail?

616
00:49:58.334 --> 00:49:59.354
You never fail.

617
00:50:22.258 --> 00:50:24.163
Are you ready for our dance?

618
00:50:33.365 --> 00:50:36.154
Is it him?  Is that the first son of Odin?

619
00:50:37.772 --> 00:50:39.001
Heimdall. your eyes!?

620
00:50:39.072 --> 00:50:41.372
Oh. they see everything.

621
00:50:41.807 --> 00:50:43.916
They see you leading us to Hel.

622
00:50:44.911 --> 00:50:45.911
Wake up!

623
00:50:49.285 --> 00:50:52.738
The war's over. Steve.  We can go home!

624
00:50:55.220 --> 00:50:56.220
Imagine it!

625
00:51:04.963 --> 00:51:09.813
- I can still save you.
- We are all dead.  Can you not see?

626
00:51:14.782 --> 00:51:16.382
You're a destroyer. Odinson.

627
00:51:20.758 --> 00:51:22.595
See where your power leads.

628
00:51:33.429 --> 00:51:34.429
Sloppy.

629
00:51:35.562 --> 00:51:36.855
Pretending to fail.

630
00:51:38.399 --> 00:51:40.168
The ceremony is necessary.

631
00:51:41.568 --> 00:51:44.221
for you to take your place in the world.

632
00:51:44.301 --> 00:51:47.566
- I have no place in the world.
- Exactly.

633
00:51:51.914 --> 00:51:54.014
- What can I do?
- Ah. it hurts.

634
00:51:55.283 --> 00:51:57.496
- I'm gonna kill him.  I'll be right back.
- No.

635
00:51:57.552 --> 00:52:00.117
I'm over it.  I want...

636
00:52:03.322 --> 00:52:05.091
I want to finish the plan.

637
00:52:06.226 --> 00:52:07.519
I want the big one.

638
00:52:18.807 --> 00:52:21.324
Ah! The Vibranium's getting away.

639
00:52:21.541 --> 00:52:22.982
And you're not going anywhere.

640
00:52:22.999 --> 00:52:26.699
Of course not.  I'm already there.  You'll catch on.

641
00:52:26.783 --> 00:52:29.912
But first. you might need to catch Dr. Banner.

642
00:52:44.263 --> 00:52:46.372
News or footage. keyword: Hulk.

643
00:52:50.656 --> 00:52:53.005
Natasha. I could really use a lullaby.

644
00:52:53.072 --> 00:52:55.113
Well. that's not gonna happen.  Not for a while.

645
00:52:56.209 --> 00:52:57.774
The whole team is down.

646
00:52:58.946 --> 00:52:59.946
You got no back up here.

647
00:53:01.147 --> 00:53:02.147
I'm calling in VERONICA.

648
00:53:10.756 --> 00:53:12.321
All units. all units...

649
00:53:12.524 --> 00:53:14.648
- Need backup!
- Whoa!  Need backup!

650
00:53:15.756 --> 00:53:17.056
You tell 'em!

651
00:53:19.597 --> 00:53:21.297
Aah!  Run!  Run!

652
00:53:33.750 --> 00:53:34.750
Raaar!

653
00:53:36.110 --> 00:53:37.410
Get back!

654
00:53:54.803 --> 00:53:56.103
Go!

655
00:53:56.305 --> 00:53:57.870
Okay. move in. move in!

656
00:54:34.973 --> 00:54:37.150
All right everybody. stand down!

657
00:54:43.983 --> 00:54:47.765
You listening?  That little witch is messing with your mind.

658
00:54:47.786 --> 00:54:50.319
You're stronger than her. you're smarter than her. you're Bruce Banner.

659
00:54:51.057 --> 00:54:51.757
Raaaar!

660
00:54:51.757 --> 00:54:54.954
Right. right. right. don't mention puny Banner.

661
00:54:58.968 --> 00:54:59.968
Okay.

662
00:55:21.290 --> 00:55:23.467
In the back?  Dick move. Banner.

663
00:55:36.038 --> 00:55:37.603
VERONICA. gimme a hand.

664
00:56:04.547 --> 00:56:08.016
Go to sleep. go to sleep. go to sleep!

665
00:56:15.879 --> 00:56:18.036
Okay. pal. we're gonna get you out of town.

666
00:56:19.615 --> 00:56:21.452
No. not that way. not that way!

667
00:56:29.256 --> 00:56:32.056
C'mon!  Bruce. you gotta work with me!

668
00:56:45.380 --> 00:56:46.380
Everybody out!

669
00:56:52.678 --> 00:56:53.678
Going to get ugly!

670
00:57:03.288 --> 00:57:04.288
I'm sorry.

671
00:57:18.737 --> 00:57:22.206
- Damage report.
- (bzzzt).
- It's comprehensive.

672
00:57:22.407 --> 00:57:23.631
Show me something.

673
00:57:34.324 --> 00:57:36.773
How quickly can we buy this building?

674
00:58:08.593 --> 00:58:10.158
Go. move. move. move. move!

675
00:58:19.663 --> 00:58:20.663
Raar!  Raaaar!

676
00:59:04.644 --> 00:59:08.405
The news is loving you guys.  Nobody else is.

677
00:59:09.583 --> 00:59:14.281
There's been no official call for Banner's arrest. but it's in the air.

678
00:59:14.321 --> 00:59:15.954
Stark Relief Foundation?

679
00:59:16.194 --> 00:59:17.523
Already on the scene.

680
00:59:17.593 --> 00:59:21.593
- How's the team?
- Everyone's...we took a hit.

681
00:59:22.264 --> 00:59:25.393
- We'll shake it off.
- Well for now I'd stay in stealth mode.

682
00:59:26.032 --> 00:59:27.665
And stay away from here.

683
00:59:28.300 --> 00:59:29.456
So. run and hide?

684
00:59:30.471 --> 00:59:34.689
Until we can find Ultron. I don't have a lot else to offer.

685
00:59:35.810 --> 00:59:36.810
Neither do we.

686
00:59:43.681 --> 00:59:45.382
Hey. you wanna switch out?

687
00:59:46.083 --> 00:59:47.083
No. I'm good.

688
00:59:47.620 --> 00:59:51.766
If you wanna get some kip. now's a good time. 'cause there's still a few hours out.

689
00:59:51.793 --> 00:59:53.358
A few hours from...where?

690
00:59:53.560 --> 00:59:54.560
A safe house.

691
01:00:21.188 --> 01:00:23.705
- What is this place?
- A safe house.

692
01:00:24.859 --> 01:00:25.859
Let's hope.

693
01:00:31.313 --> 01:00:33.901
Honey.  I'm home.

694
01:00:37.404 --> 01:00:38.004
Hi.

695
01:00:38.072 --> 01:00:40.072
- Company.  Sorry didn't call ahead.
- Hey.

696
01:00:42.342 --> 01:00:44.083
This is an agent of some kind.

697
01:00:44.140 --> 01:00:45.841
Gentleman. this is Laura.

698
01:00:46.944 --> 01:00:48.441
I know all your names.

699
01:00:51.685 --> 01:00:52.705
Oooh. incoming.

700
01:00:53.455 --> 01:00:56.052
- Ah!
- Dad!
- I see her!  Hey buddy!

701
01:00:56.321 --> 01:00:58.714
How you guys doing?  Ooh...

702
01:00:58.792 --> 01:01:01.229
- These are...smaller agents.
- ...look at your face!

703
01:01:01.260 --> 01:01:04.389
- Oh my goodness!
- Did you bring Auntie Nat?

704
01:01:04.566 --> 01:01:06.947
Why don't you hug her and find out?

705
01:01:08.504 --> 01:01:13.515
- Sorry for barging in on you.
- Yeah. we woulda called ahead. but we were busy having no idea that you existed.

706
01:01:13.574 --> 01:01:16.711
Yeah. well Fury helped me set this up when I joined.

707
01:01:16.740 --> 01:01:20.418
He kept it off SHIELD's files. I'd like to keep it that way.

708
01:01:20.582 --> 01:01:23.467
- I figure it's a good place to lay low.
- Honey.

709
01:01:24.248 --> 01:01:27.248
Ah. I missed you.  How's little Natasha. huh?

710
01:01:27.554 --> 01:01:29.442
She is...

711
01:01:30.861 --> 01:01:31.861
...Nathaniel.

712
01:01:34.963 --> 01:01:35.963
Traitor.

713
01:01:36.760 --> 01:01:37.760
(chatter)

714
01:01:45.304 --> 01:01:48.705
- Somebody's getting bigger. huh?
- Somebody's getting excited to have a new baby brother.
- (chatter continues)

715
01:01:51.676 --> 01:01:52.576
Thor.

716
01:01:52.613 --> 01:01:57.511
I saw something in that dream.  I need answers.  I won't find them here.

717
01:02:07.858 --> 01:02:09.151
We can go home.

718
01:02:20.606 --> 01:02:25.368
See you worried for nothing.  Can't even feel the difference. can you?

719
01:02:27.312 --> 01:02:31.070
If they're sleeping here. some of them are gonna have to double up.

720
01:02:31.452 --> 01:02:34.309
Heh heh heh.  Yeah. that's not gonna sell.

721
01:02:37.222 --> 01:02:41.531
What about Nat. and Dr. Banner?  How long has that been going on?

722
01:02:42.693 --> 01:02:43.593
Has what?

723
01:02:43.630 --> 01:02:46.267
Ha ha ha!  You are so cute.

724
01:02:46.766 --> 01:02:47.922
Nat and...and Banner?

725
01:02:48.904 --> 01:02:51.729
I'll explain when you're older.  "Hawkeye."

726
01:02:51.769 --> 01:02:52.769
Oh.  Okay.

727
01:02:55.106 --> 01:02:57.963
It's bad. right?  Nat seems really shaken.

728
01:02:59.477 --> 01:03:03.695
Ultron has these allies. these uh. kids. they're punks really.

729
01:03:06.919 --> 01:03:10.524
They carry a big damn stick and Nat took a serious hit.

730
01:03:11.809 --> 01:03:14.506
Someone's gonna have to teach 'em some manners.

731
01:03:14.595 --> 01:03:16.195
And that someone be you.

732
01:03:17.494 --> 01:03:21.916
You know I totally support your Avenging.  I couldn't be prouder.

733
01:03:23.669 --> 01:03:27.086
But I see those guys. those..."gods."

734
01:03:29.606 --> 01:03:31.579
You don't think they need me.

735
01:03:31.987 --> 01:03:33.075
I think they do.

736
01:03:33.712 --> 01:03:35.277
Which is a lot scarier.

737
01:03:36.916 --> 01:03:37.936
They're a mess.

738
01:03:39.818 --> 01:03:40.818
Yeah.

739
01:03:41.151 --> 01:03:42.784
I guess they're my mess.

740
01:03:44.265 --> 01:03:50.035
You need to be sure that this team is really a team and that they have your back.

741
01:03:54.069 --> 01:03:55.069
Things are changing for us.

742
01:03:56.634 --> 01:04:01.067
In a few months time. you and me are gonna be outnumbered.

743
01:04:02.039 --> 01:04:03.039
I need...

744
01:04:06.616 --> 01:04:07.616
Just be sure.

745
01:04:09.547 --> 01:04:10.547
Yes. ma'am.

746
01:04:19.553 --> 01:04:21.322
I can feel the difference.

747
01:04:28.165 --> 01:04:29.321
(speaking Korean)

748
01:04:34.806 --> 01:04:37.187
Scream. and your entire staff dies.

749
01:04:39.113 --> 01:04:42.713
I could've killed you. Helen. the night we met.  I didn't.

750
01:04:42.749 --> 01:04:44.058
Do you expect a thank you note?

751
01:04:44.317 --> 01:04:46.018
I expect you to know why.

752
01:04:48.176 --> 01:04:49.076
The cradle.

753
01:04:49.148 --> 01:04:51.257
"This is the next thing. Tony."

754
01:04:51.322 --> 01:04:52.819
This...is the next me.

755
01:04:54.184 --> 01:04:58.810
The regeneration cradle prints tissue. it can't build a living body.

756
01:04:58.833 --> 01:04:59.989
It can.  You can.

757
01:05:00.533 --> 01:05:02.030
You lacked the materials.

758
01:05:04.212 --> 01:05:06.389
You're a brilliant woman. Helen.

759
01:05:08.240 --> 01:05:12.117
But we all have room to improve.

760
01:05:31.897 --> 01:05:32.897
Oh.

761
01:05:33.534 --> 01:05:36.051
I didn't realize you were waiting.

762
01:05:36.240 --> 01:05:38.281
I would've joined you. but uh.

763
01:05:38.770 --> 01:05:40.947
it didn't seem like the right time.

764
01:05:41.705 --> 01:05:43.610
They used up all the hot water.

765
01:05:44.209 --> 01:05:45.774
I should've joined you.

766
01:05:46.244 --> 01:05:47.468
Missed our window.

767
01:05:48.380 --> 01:05:49.380
Did we?

768
01:05:53.246 --> 01:05:54.811
The world just saw the Hulk.

769
01:05:56.522 --> 01:05:58.835
The real Hulk. for the first time.

770
01:06:02.395 --> 01:06:03.596
You know I have to leave.

771
01:06:03.630 --> 01:06:06.011
But you assume that I have to stay?

772
01:06:06.832 --> 01:06:11.118
I had this. um. dream.  The kind that seems normal at the time.

773
01:06:12.671 --> 01:06:15.732
- But when you wake...
- What did you dream?

774
01:06:16.609 --> 01:06:17.765
That I was an Avenger.

775
01:06:20.112 --> 01:06:23.922
That I was anything more than the assassin they made me.

776
01:06:25.886 --> 01:06:28.607
I think you're being harder on yourself.

777
01:06:30.189 --> 01:06:32.638
Here I was hoping that was your job.

778
01:06:35.669 --> 01:06:36.962
What are you doing?

779
01:06:38.631 --> 01:06:39.992
I'm running with it.

780
01:06:41.902 --> 01:06:42.902
With you.

781
01:06:44.434 --> 01:06:48.591
If running's the plan. as far as you want.

782
01:06:51.177 --> 01:06:52.878
Are you out of your mind?

783
01:06:58.587 --> 01:07:00.568
I want you to understand that I'm...

784
01:07:00.577 --> 01:07:01.577
Natasha.

785
01:07:02.902 --> 01:07:03.922
Where can I go?

786
01:07:05.203 --> 01:07:07.620
Where in the world am I not a threat?

787
01:07:07.653 --> 01:07:09.222
You're not a threat to me.

788
01:07:09.255 --> 01:07:10.255
You sure?

789
01:07:10.721 --> 01:07:15.222
Even if I didn't just...there's no future with me.

790
01:07:17.265 --> 01:07:22.118
I can't ever...I can't have this. kids.

791
01:07:23.034 --> 01:07:25.734
do the math. I physically can't.

792
01:07:27.169 --> 01:07:28.169
Neither can I.

793
01:07:33.610 --> 01:07:39.360
In the Red Room. where I was trained. where I was raised. um.

794
01:07:40.918 --> 01:07:43.095
they have a graduation ceremony.

795
01:07:45.556 --> 01:07:46.849
They sterilize you.

796
01:07:50.131 --> 01:07:51.151
It's efficient.

797
01:07:54.533 --> 01:07:56.574
One less thing to worry about.

798
01:07:58.139 --> 01:08:01.676
The one thing that might matter more than a mission.

799
01:08:03.865 --> 01:08:05.498
Makes everything easier.

800
01:08:07.012 --> 01:08:08.012
Even killing.

801
01:08:13.516 --> 01:08:17.053
You still think you're the only monster on the team?

802
01:08:22.695 --> 01:08:24.192
What. so we disappear?

803
01:08:30.934 --> 01:08:34.131
Thor didn't say where he was going for answers?

804
01:08:34.146 --> 01:08:37.139
Sometimes my teammates don't tell me things.

805
01:08:37.312 --> 01:08:39.573
I was kinda hoping Thor would be the exception.

806
01:08:39.612 --> 01:08:41.041
Yeah.  Give him time.

807
01:08:41.679 --> 01:08:44.876
We don't know what the Maximoff kid showed him.

808
01:08:45.319 --> 01:08:49.119
"Earth's Mightiest Heroes."  Pulled us apart like cotton candy.

809
01:08:49.487 --> 01:08:51.868
Seems like you walked away all right.

810
01:08:53.624 --> 01:08:54.848
Is that a problem?

811
01:08:54.860 --> 01:08:57.581
I don't trust a guy without a dark side.

812
01:08:58.262 --> 01:08:59.759
Call me old fashioned.

813
01:08:59.799 --> 01:09:02.192
Well let's just say you haven't seen it yet.

814
01:09:02.269 --> 01:09:05.170
You know Ultron is trying to tear us apart. right?

815
01:09:05.269 --> 01:09:08.434
Well I guess you'd know.  Whether you tell us is a bit of a question.

816
01:09:08.575 --> 01:09:10.720
- Banner and I were doing research.
- That would affect the team.

817
01:09:10.743 --> 01:09:13.776
That would end the team.  Isn't that the mission?

818
01:09:13.778 --> 01:09:19.016
Isn't that the "why we fight." so we can end the fight. so we get to go home?

819
01:09:20.086 --> 01:09:25.256
Every time someone tries to win a war before it starts. innocent people die.

820
01:09:25.257 --> 01:09:26.257
Every time.

821
01:09:27.761 --> 01:09:34.461
I'm sorry.  Mr. Stark. uh. Clint said you wouldn't mind. but. our tractor doesn't seem to want to start at all.

822
01:09:35.569 --> 01:09:38.342
- I thought maybe you might...
- Yeah. I'll give it a kick.

823
01:09:41.005 --> 01:09:42.638
Don't take from my pile.

824
01:09:52.851 --> 01:09:53.851
Hello. dear.

825
01:09:56.889 --> 01:09:58.182
Tell me everything.

826
01:09:59.326 --> 01:10:00.326
What ails you?

827
01:10:01.362 --> 01:10:02.362
Do me a favor.

828
01:10:04.063 --> 01:10:05.968
Try not to bring it to life.

829
01:10:06.382 --> 01:10:08.627
Ah. Mrs. Barton. you little minx.

830
01:10:08.699 --> 01:10:10.984
I get it. Maria Hill called you right?

831
01:10:11.038 --> 01:10:12.583
Was she ever not working for you?

832
01:10:12.603 --> 01:10:14.236
Artificial Intelligence.

833
01:10:15.172 --> 01:10:18.594
- You never even hesitated.
- Look. it's been a really long day.

834
01:10:18.677 --> 01:10:22.638
like. Eugene O'Neill long. so how's about we skip to the part where you're useful?

835
01:10:22.647 --> 01:10:25.297
Look me in the eye and tell me you're going to shut him down.

836
01:10:25.316 --> 01:10:28.174
- You're not the director of me.
- I'm not the director of anybody.

837
01:10:28.754 --> 01:10:33.147
I'm just an old man. who cares very much about you.

838
01:10:35.462 --> 01:10:37.662
And I'm the man who killed the Avengers.

839
01:10:39.565 --> 01:10:40.565
I saw it.

840
01:10:40.835 --> 01:10:43.052
I didn't tell the team.  How could I?

841
01:10:43.060 --> 01:10:47.074
I saw them all dead. Nick.  Felt it.  The whole world. too.

842
01:10:47.941 --> 01:10:49.234
It's because of me.

843
01:10:50.274 --> 01:10:51.294
I wasn't ready.

844
01:10:52.512 --> 01:10:54.145
I didn't do all I could.

845
01:10:55.148 --> 01:10:57.665
The Maximoff girl. she's working you. Stark.

846
01:10:57.813 --> 01:11:00.710
- Playing on your fear.
- I wasn't tricked. I was shown.

847
01:11:01.384 --> 01:11:03.705
It wasn't a nightmare. it was my legacy.

848
01:11:03.755 --> 01:11:05.116
The end of the path I started us on.

849
01:11:07.173 --> 01:11:11.051
You come up with some pretty impressive inventions. Tony.

850
01:11:11.137 --> 01:11:12.634
War isn't one of them.

851
01:11:16.371 --> 01:11:20.793
I watched my friends die.  You'd think that'd be as bad as it gets. right?  Pfft.

852
01:11:21.708 --> 01:11:22.708
Nope.

853
01:11:24.208 --> 01:11:25.705
Wasn't the worst part.

854
01:11:25.910 --> 01:11:28.359
The worst part...is that you didn't.

855
01:11:35.555 --> 01:11:36.984
I'll see you tonight.

856
01:11:39.172 --> 01:11:40.260
I like the look.

857
01:11:41.568 --> 01:11:44.873
If you're going for inconspicuous. though. near miss.

858
01:11:44.897 --> 01:11:46.153
I need your help.

859
01:11:46.164 --> 01:11:47.429
It's nice to be needed.

860
01:11:47.497 --> 01:11:48.517
It's dangerous.

861
01:11:49.235 --> 01:11:51.480
I'd be disappointed if it wasn't.

862
01:11:54.272 --> 01:11:57.645
Ultron took you folks out of play to buy himself time.

863
01:11:57.712 --> 01:12:00.612
My contacts all say he's building something.

864
01:12:00.647 --> 01:12:04.917
The amount of Vibranium he made off with. I don't think it's just one thing.

865
01:12:04.985 --> 01:12:06.285
What about Ultron himself?

866
01:12:06.817 --> 01:12:12.407
Ah.  He's easy to track. he's everywhere.  Guy's multiplying faster than a Catholic rabbit.

867
01:12:12.492 --> 01:12:15.721
Still doesn't help us get an angle on any of his plans though.

868
01:12:15.761 --> 01:12:17.374
- He still going after launch codes?
- Yes. he is.

869
01:12:17.461 --> 01:12:19.161
but he's not making any headway.

870
01:12:19.396 --> 01:12:22.296
I cracked the Pentagon's firewall in high school on a dare.

871
01:12:22.395 --> 01:12:25.395
Yeah. well. I contacted our friends at the NEXUS about that.

872
01:12:25.396 --> 01:12:27.696
- NEXUS?
- It's the world internet hub in Oslo.

873
01:12:27.705 --> 01:12:31.105
every byte of data flows through there. fastest access on earth.

874
01:12:31.177 --> 01:12:32.470
So what'd they say?

875
01:12:32.577 --> 01:12:34.250
He's fixated on the missiles.

876
01:12:34.294 --> 01:12:36.519
But the codes are constantly being changed.

877
01:12:36.615 --> 01:12:37.615
By whom?

878
01:12:38.952 --> 01:12:40.040
Parties unknown.

879
01:12:40.217 --> 01:12:41.105
We have an ally?

880
01:12:41.120 --> 01:12:44.021
Ultron's got an enemy.  That's not the same thing.

881
01:12:44.290 --> 01:12:45.987
Still. I'd pay folding money to know who it is.

882
01:12:46.206 --> 01:12:48.794
I might need to visit Oslo.  Find our "unknown."

883
01:12:48.828 --> 01:12:53.063
Well. this is good times. boss. but I was kind of hoping when I saw you. you'd have more than that.

884
01:12:53.133 --> 01:12:55.157
I do.  I have you.

885
01:12:56.203 --> 01:12:59.259
Back in the day. I had eyes everywhere. ears everywhere else.

886
01:12:59.620 --> 01:13:02.020
You kids had all the tech you could dream of.

887
01:13:03.409 --> 01:13:09.709
Here we all are. back on earth. with nothing but our wit. and our will to save the world.

888
01:13:11.149 --> 01:13:15.249
Ultron says the Avengers are the only thing between him and his mission.

889
01:13:15.422 --> 01:13:21.122
And whether or not he admits it. his mission is global destruction.

890
01:13:21.292 --> 01:13:23.592
All this. laid in a grave.

891
01:13:25.531 --> 01:13:26.531
So stand.

892
01:13:27.932 --> 01:13:29.837
Outwit the platinum bastard.

893
01:13:30.361 --> 01:13:32.378
Steve doesn't like that kind of talk.

894
01:13:32.407 --> 01:13:33.672
You know what. Romanoff?

895
01:13:34.105 --> 01:13:35.534
So what does he want?

896
01:13:37.043 --> 01:13:40.243
To become better.  Better than us.

897
01:13:40.644 --> 01:13:42.345
He keeps building bodies.

898
01:13:42.414 --> 01:13:47.428
Person bodies.  The human form is inefficient. biologically speaking. we're outmoded.

899
01:13:47.521 --> 01:13:49.121
But he keeps coming back to it.

900
01:13:50.053 --> 01:13:53.323
When you two programmed him to protect the human race. you amazingly failed.

901
01:13:53.327 --> 01:13:57.027
They don't need to be protected.  They need to evolve.

902
01:13:59.763 --> 01:14:02.432
- Ultron's going to evolve.
- How?

903
01:14:04.434 --> 01:14:07.291
Has anyone been in contact with Helen Cho?

904
01:14:11.100 --> 01:14:12.120
It's beautiful.

905
01:14:13.015 --> 01:14:17.733
The Vibranium atoms aren't just compatible with the tissue cells. they're binding them.

906
01:14:17.818 --> 01:14:19.395
And SHIELD never even thought...

907
01:14:19.417 --> 01:14:24.117
The most versatile substance on the planet and they used it to make a frisbee.

908
01:14:24.190 --> 01:14:28.614
Typical of humans.  They scratch the surface and never think...

909
01:14:30.061 --> 01:14:31.285
...to look within.

910
01:14:42.108 --> 01:14:45.818
- I'll take Natasha and Clint.
- All right.  Strictly recon.

911
01:14:45.913 --> 01:14:46.913
I'll hit the NEXUS. I'll join you as soon as I can.

912
01:14:47.481 --> 01:14:48.966
If Ultron is really building a body...

913
01:14:49.012 --> 01:14:52.109
He'll be more powerful than any of us.  Maybe all of us.

914
01:14:52.985 --> 01:14:55.094
An android designed by a robot.

915
01:14:55.120 --> 01:14:58.334
You know I really miss the days when the weirdest thing science ever created was me.

916
01:14:58.357 --> 01:15:01.802
I'll drop Banner off at the tower.  Do you mind if I borrow Ms. Hill?

917
01:15:01.829 --> 01:15:04.617
She's all yours.  Apparently.  What are you gonna do?

918
01:15:05.233 --> 01:15:07.990
I don't know.  Something dramatic. I hope.

919
01:15:11.636 --> 01:15:13.745
I'm gonna finish re-flooring that sunroom as soon as I get back.

920
01:15:15.339 --> 01:15:18.325
Yeah. then you'll find another part of the house to tear apart.

921
01:15:18.512 --> 01:15:19.512
No.

922
01:15:20.243 --> 01:15:21.740
It's the last project.

923
01:15:23.279 --> 01:15:24.279
I Promise.

924
01:15:42.769 --> 01:15:43.769
This is it.

925
01:15:45.572 --> 01:15:46.865
The Water of Sight.

926
01:15:50.008 --> 01:15:52.525
In every realm. there's a reflection.

927
01:15:53.713 --> 01:15:58.813
If the water spirits accept me. I can return to my dream. and find what I missed.

928
01:15:59.819 --> 01:16:03.424
The men who enter that water...the legends don't end well.

929
01:16:05.491 --> 01:16:08.064
A hacker who's faster than Ultron?  He could be anywhere.

930
01:16:08.092 --> 01:16:13.492
And as this is the center of everything. I'm just a guy looking for a needle in the world's biggest haystack.

931
01:16:14.864 --> 01:16:16.495
How do you find it?

932
01:16:16.700 --> 01:16:18.945
Pretty simple.  You bring a magnet.

933
01:16:20.739 --> 01:16:24.159
(sings) Oh. I'm decrypting nuclear codes and you don't want me to.

934
01:16:26.410 --> 01:16:27.498
Come and get me.

935
01:16:40.290 --> 01:16:41.290
Wake up!

936
01:16:48.301 --> 01:16:49.301
Thor!

937
01:16:49.870 --> 01:16:50.870
Extinction.

938
01:17:04.620 --> 01:17:08.373
Cellular cohesion will take a few hours. but we can initiate the consciousness stream.

939
01:17:10.121 --> 01:17:13.621
We're uploading your cerebral matrix...now.

940
01:17:15.626 --> 01:17:16.646
I can read him.

941
01:17:17.863 --> 01:17:19.583
He is dreaming.

942
01:17:19.965 --> 01:17:25.611
I wouldn't call it dreams.  It's Ultron's base consciousness.  Informational noise.  Soon...

943
01:17:25.638 --> 01:17:28.438
How soon?  I'm not being pushy.

944
01:17:28.474 --> 01:17:34.874
We're imprinting a physical brain.  There are no shortcuts.  Even if you imagined...

945
01:17:35.147 --> 01:17:36.147
Aaah!

946
01:17:39.786 --> 01:17:40.786
He...

947
01:17:43.854 --> 01:17:46.795
- How could you?
- How could I what?

948
01:17:46.872 --> 01:17:49.525
You said we would destroy the Avengers.

949
01:17:50.227 --> 01:17:53.220
- Make a better world.
- It will be better.

950
01:17:53.266 --> 01:17:55.266
- When everyone is dead.
- That is not...!

951
01:17:55.934 --> 01:17:59.607
The human race will have every opportunity to improve.

952
01:18:00.939 --> 01:18:02.163
And if they don't?

953
01:18:02.175 --> 01:18:03.175
Ask Noah.

954
01:18:04.473 --> 01:18:05.561
You're a madman.

955
01:18:06.108 --> 01:18:12.230
There were more than a dozen extinction level events before even the dinosaurs got theirs.

956
01:18:12.587 --> 01:18:19.177
When the Earth starts to settle. God throws a stone at it. and believe me. he's winding up.

957
01:18:20.793 --> 01:18:24.317
We have to evolve.  There's no room for the weak.

958
01:18:24.361 --> 01:18:28.361
And who decides who's weak?

959
01:18:28.749 --> 01:18:32.386
Life.  Life always decides.

960
01:18:35.703 --> 01:18:39.759
There's incoming.  The Quinjet.  We have to move.

961
01:18:39.844 --> 01:18:41.273
That's not a problem.

962
01:18:47.350 --> 01:18:48.779
Uh. wait. guys!  I...

963
01:18:53.061 --> 01:18:57.007
They don't understand.  When they see. they'll understand.

964
01:18:57.430 --> 01:19:00.639
I just need a little more...time.

965
01:19:12.176 --> 01:19:14.176
Two minutes.  Stay close.

966
01:19:21.284 --> 01:19:22.284
Dr. Cho!

967
01:19:26.292 --> 01:19:28.109
He's uploading himself into the body.

968
01:19:28.203 --> 01:19:29.203
Where?

969
01:19:30.764 --> 01:19:33.417
The real power is inside the cradle.

970
01:19:33.799 --> 01:19:36.884
The gem.  Its power is uncontainable.

971
01:19:38.873 --> 01:19:40.642
You can't just blow it up.

972
01:19:42.237 --> 01:19:43.786
You have to get the cradle to Stark.

973
01:19:43.878 --> 01:19:45.511
First I have to find it.

974
01:19:45.542 --> 01:19:46.542
Go.

975
01:19:46.848 --> 01:19:48.141
- Did you guys copy that?
- We did.

976
01:19:48.813 --> 01:19:55.191
I got a private jet taking off. across town. no manifest.  That could be him.

977
01:19:55.520 --> 01:19:58.520
There.  It's the truck from the lab.  Right above you. Cap.

978
01:19:58.625 --> 01:20:00.394
On the loop by the bridge.

979
01:20:01.162 --> 01:20:04.235
It's them.  I got three with the cradle. one in the cab.

980
01:20:04.327 --> 01:20:06.132
I could take out the driver.

981
01:20:06.196 --> 01:20:08.878
Negative!  If that truck crashes. the gem could level the city.

982
01:20:08.968 --> 01:20:10.268
We need to draw out Ultron.

983
01:20:20.313 --> 01:20:21.401
No. no no no no.

984
01:20:24.018 --> 01:20:25.038
Leave me alone!

985
01:20:33.494 --> 01:20:36.767
Well he's definitely unhappy!  I'm gonna try and keep him that way.

986
01:20:36.962 --> 01:20:39.139
You're not a match for him. Cap.

987
01:20:39.896 --> 01:20:40.916
Thanks. Barton.

988
01:21:02.858 --> 01:21:04.967
You know what's in that cradle?

989
01:21:05.559 --> 01:21:09.300
The power to make real change.  And that terrifies you.

990
01:21:09.327 --> 01:21:11.368
I wouldn't call it a comfort.

991
01:21:14.064 --> 01:21:15.064
Stop it!

992
01:21:25.245 --> 01:21:30.033
We got a window.  4. 3...  Give 'em hell.

993
01:21:40.623 --> 01:21:43.140
I'm always picking up after you boys.

994
01:21:43.428 --> 01:21:46.133
They're heading under the overpass. I've got no shot.

995
01:21:46.133 --> 01:21:47.133
Which way?

996
01:21:47.301 --> 01:21:48.301
Hard right...

997
01:21:49.292 --> 01:21:50.292
Now.

998
01:22:21.265 --> 01:22:22.885
Out of the way!  Coming through!

999
01:22:22.942 --> 01:22:24.439
Sorry. coming through!

1000
01:22:38.858 --> 01:22:39.858
Come on!

1001
01:22:41.194 --> 01:22:42.194
Clint!  Can you draw out the guards?

1002
01:22:42.625 --> 01:22:43.645
Let's find out.

1003
01:22:44.462 --> 01:22:45.462
Beep beep!

1004
01:23:04.679 --> 01:23:05.835
(Korean language)

1005
01:23:22.832 --> 01:23:26.933
They're heading back towards you.  So whatever you're going to do. do it now.

1006
01:23:31.474 --> 01:23:34.059
I'm going in.  Cap. can you keep him occupied?

1007
01:23:34.909 --> 01:23:37.222
What do you think I've been doing?

1008
01:24:19.990 --> 01:24:21.351
A package is airborne.

1009
01:24:22.924 --> 01:24:24.085
I have a clean shot.

1010
01:24:24.126 --> 01:24:26.248
- Negative.  I am still in the truck.
- What the hell are you...

1011
01:24:26.339 --> 01:24:28.439
Just be ready. I'm sending the package to you.

1012
01:24:28.512 --> 01:24:30.249
How do you want me to take it?

1013
01:24:30.298 --> 01:24:33.155
Uhh. you might wish you hadn't asked that.

1014
01:24:44.713 --> 01:24:46.278
Please.  Don't do this.

1015
01:24:47.118 --> 01:24:48.683
What choice do we have?

1016
01:24:56.703 --> 01:24:57.703
I lost him!

1017
01:24:57.794 --> 01:24:59.594
He's heading your way!

1018
01:25:04.538 --> 01:25:05.762
Nat. we gotta go.

1019
01:25:16.746 --> 01:25:18.146
- Clint!
- Nat!

1020
01:25:22.185 --> 01:25:23.341
Cap. you see Nat?

1021
01:25:24.820 --> 01:25:27.249
If you have the package. get it to Stark!  Go!

1022
01:25:27.289 --> 01:25:28.922
- Do you have eyes on Nat?
- Go!

1023
01:25:33.438 --> 01:25:34.438
Civilians in our path.

1024
01:25:35.597 --> 01:25:37.230
Can you stop this thing?

1025
01:26:16.065 --> 01:26:18.565
I'm fine.  I just need to take a minute.

1026
01:26:19.207 --> 01:26:20.824
I'm very tempted not to give you one.

1027
01:26:21.014 --> 01:26:22.619
The cradle.  Did you get it?

1028
01:26:23.147 --> 01:26:24.848
Stark'll take care of it.

1029
01:26:26.449 --> 01:26:27.449
No. he won't.

1030
01:26:31.119 --> 01:26:32.801
You don't know what you're talking about. Stark's not crazy.

1031
01:26:32.821 --> 01:26:35.214
He will do anything to make things right.

1032
01:26:40.399 --> 01:26:41.399
Stark. come in.

1033
01:26:41.836 --> 01:26:42.836
Stark.

1034
01:26:44.234 --> 01:26:45.322
Anyone on comms?

1035
01:26:45.534 --> 01:26:50.704
Ultron can't tell the difference between saving the world and destroying it.

1036
01:26:51.108 --> 01:26:53.208
Where do you think he gets that?

1037
01:26:55.987 --> 01:26:56.787
Anything on Nat?

1038
01:26:56.878 --> 01:27:00.476
Haven't heard.  But she's alive. or Ultron'd be rubbing our faces in it.

1039
01:27:00.484 --> 01:27:04.649
- This is sealed tight.
- We're going to need to access the program. break it down from within.

1040
01:27:06.222 --> 01:27:10.176
Any chance Natasha might leave you a message. outside the internet. old school spy stuff?

1041
01:27:10.727 --> 01:27:13.936
There's some nets I can cast.  Yeah. all right.  I'll find her.

1042
01:27:16.401 --> 01:27:21.639
I can work on tissue degeneration. if you can fry whatever operational system Cho implanted.

1043
01:27:22.038 --> 01:27:23.194
Yeah. about that.

1044
01:27:27.475 --> 01:27:28.275
No.

1045
01:27:28.277 --> 01:27:30.262
- You have to trust me.
- Kinda don't.

1046
01:27:30.348 --> 01:27:34.048
Our ally?  The guy protecting the military's nuclear codes?

1047
01:27:36.152 --> 01:27:37.152
I found him.

1048
01:27:37.753 --> 01:27:38.977
Hello. Dr. Banner.

1049
01:27:39.146 --> 01:27:46.493
Ultron didn't go after Jarvis 'cause he was angry.  He attacked him because he was scared of what he can do.

1050
01:27:46.764 --> 01:27:52.342
So Jarvis went underground.  Okay. scattered. dumped his memory.  But not his protocols.

1051
01:27:52.919 --> 01:27:56.041
He didn't even know he was in there. until I pieced him together.

1052
01:27:57.804 --> 01:28:04.004
So. you want me to help you put Jarvis into this thing?

1053
01:28:04.024 --> 01:28:07.848
No. of course not!  I want to help you put Jarvis in this thing.

1054
01:28:10.230 --> 01:28:13.330
We're out of my field here.  You know bio-organics better than anyone.

1055
01:28:13.955 --> 01:28:18.785
And you just assume that Jarvis's operational matrix can beat Ultron's?

1056
01:28:18.826 --> 01:28:21.014
Jarvis has been beating him from inside without knowing it.

1057
01:28:21.932 --> 01:28:28.632
This is the opportunity. we can create Ultron's perfect self. without the homicidal glitches he thinks are his winning personality.

1058
01:28:28.703 --> 01:28:31.003
- We have to.
- I believe it's worth a go.

1059
01:28:33.178 --> 01:28:37.664
No.  I'm in a loop.  I'm caught in a time loop. this is exactly where it all went wrong.

1060
01:28:37.677 --> 01:28:40.477
I know. I know.  I know what everyone's going to say. but they're already saying it.

1061
01:28:42.185 --> 01:28:49.091
We're mad scientists.  We're monsters. buddy.  You gotta own it.  Make a stand.

1062
01:28:54.128 --> 01:28:57.752
It's not a loop.  It's the end of the line.

1063
01:29:19.058 --> 01:29:23.558
I was unsure you'd wake up.  I hoped you would. I wanted to show you.

1064
01:29:24.895 --> 01:29:27.396
I don't have anyone else.

1065
01:29:28.966 --> 01:29:32.635
I think a lot about meteors. the purity of them.

1066
01:29:33.439 --> 01:29:36.068
"Boom!". the end. start again.

1067
01:29:36.472 --> 01:29:40.689
The world made clean for the new man to rebuild.

1068
01:29:41.670 --> 01:29:43.303
I was meant to be new.

1069
01:29:43.749 --> 01:29:45.654
I was meant to be beautiful.

1070
01:29:47.695 --> 01:29:52.741
The world would've looked to the sky and seen hope. seen mercy.

1071
01:29:53.724 --> 01:29:57.057
Instead they'll look up in horror because of you.

1072
01:29:57.494 --> 01:30:00.895
You've wounded me.  I give you full marks for that.

1073
01:30:02.000 --> 01:30:05.597
But. like the man said. "What doesn't kill me...

1074
01:30:10.307 --> 01:30:12.776
...just makes me stronger!"

1075
01:30:51.881 --> 01:30:53.922
This framework is not compatible.

1076
01:30:54.016 --> 01:30:55.716
The genetic coding tower's at 97 percent.

1077
01:30:57.351 --> 01:31:01.905
You have got to upload that schematic in the next three minutes.

1078
01:31:02.459 --> 01:31:04.092
I'm gonna say this once.

1079
01:31:04.161 --> 01:31:05.249
How about "nonce"?

1080
01:31:05.326 --> 01:31:06.326
Shut it down.

1081
01:31:06.328 --> 01:31:07.661
Nope.  Not gonna happen.

1082
01:31:07.697 --> 01:31:10.158
- You don't know what you're doing.
- And you do?  She's not in your head?

1083
01:31:11.167 --> 01:31:14.636
- I know you're angry.
- No. we're way past that.

1084
01:31:14.938 --> 01:31:17.652
I could choke the life out of you and never change a shade.

1085
01:31:17.694 --> 01:31:19.144
Banner. after everything that's happened...

1086
01:31:19.148 --> 01:31:22.985
- That's nothing compared to what's coming.
- You don't know what's in there.  The creature...
- This isn't a game.

1087
01:31:26.547 --> 01:31:29.748
No. no.  Go on.  You were saying?

1088
01:31:36.860 --> 01:31:37.860
Pietro!

1089
01:31:39.495 --> 01:31:41.808
What?  You didn't see that coming?

1090
01:31:44.169 --> 01:31:46.638
I'm re-routing the upload.

1091
01:31:51.543 --> 01:31:53.108
Go ahead.  Piss me off.

1092
01:32:05.422 --> 01:32:06.422
Wait!

1093
01:33:31.192 --> 01:33:32.192
I'm sorry.  That was...

1094
01:33:34.175 --> 01:33:35.175
...odd.

1095
01:33:35.745 --> 01:33:36.745
Thank you.

1096
01:33:42.228 --> 01:33:43.228
Thor.

1097
01:33:43.685 --> 01:33:45.250
You helped create this?

1098
01:33:45.689 --> 01:33:51.879
I've had a vision.  A whirlpool that  sucks in all hope of life and at it's center is that.

1099
01:33:52.129 --> 01:33:52.729
What. the gem?

1100
01:33:52.863 --> 01:33:59.263
It's the Mind Stone.  It's one of the six Infinity Stones. the greatest power in the universe. unparalleled in its destructive capabilities.

1101
01:33:59.334 --> 01:34:01.327
- Then why would you bring it to...
- Because Stark is right.

1102
01:34:01.406 --> 01:34:03.719
Oh. it's definitely the end times.

1103
01:34:03.908 --> 01:34:06.221
- The Avengers cannot defeat Ultron.
- Not alone.

1104
01:34:07.312 --> 01:34:09.401
Why does your "vision" sound like Jarvis?

1105
01:34:09.477 --> 01:34:13.674
We reconfigured Jarvis' matrix to create something new.

1106
01:34:14.185 --> 01:34:16.262
I think I've had my fill of new.

1107
01:34:16.287 --> 01:34:19.620
- You think I'm a child of Ultron?
- You're not?

1108
01:34:21.492 --> 01:34:28.212
I'm not Ultron.  I'm not Jarvis.  I am...

1109
01:34:28.261 --> 01:34:29.261
I am.

1110
01:34:31.734 --> 01:34:34.559
I looked in your head and saw annihilation.

1111
01:34:34.601 --> 01:34:35.601
Look again.

1112
01:34:36.303 --> 01:34:38.932
Yeah.  Her seal of approval means jack to me.

1113
01:34:39.071 --> 01:34:45.136
Their powers.  The horrors in our heads.  Ultron himself.  They all came from the Mind Stone. and they're nothing compared to what it can unleash.

1114
01:34:45.149 --> 01:34:46.149
But with it on our side...

1115
01:34:46.580 --> 01:34:48.468
Is it?  Are you?

1116
01:34:50.384 --> 01:34:51.384
On our side?

1117
01:34:53.156 --> 01:34:55.197
I don't think it's that simple.

1118
01:34:55.556 --> 01:34:58.141
Well it better get real simple real soon.

1119
01:34:58.960 --> 01:35:04.193
I'm on the side of life.  Ultron isn't.  He will end it all.

1120
01:35:04.867 --> 01:35:07.044
- What's he waiting for?
- You.

1121
01:35:07.704 --> 01:35:09.465
- Where?
- Sokovia.

1122
01:35:09.541 --> 01:35:11.206
He's got Nat there too.

1123
01:35:13.011 --> 01:35:14.848
If we're wrong about you...

1124
01:35:16.846 --> 01:35:18.846
...if you're the monster that Ultron made you to be...

1125
01:35:19.949 --> 01:35:21.805
What will you do?

1126
01:35:28.057 --> 01:35:33.198
I don't want to kill Ultron.  He's unique.  And he's in pain.

1127
01:35:35.782 --> 01:35:40.136
But that pain will roll over the earth. so he must be destroyed.

1128
01:35:40.203 --> 01:35:45.103
Every form he's built. every trace of his presence on the 'net. we have to act now.

1129
01:35:46.142 --> 01:35:49.791
And not one of us can do it without the others.

1130
01:35:52.282 --> 01:35:55.682
Maybe I am a monster.  I don't think I'd know if I were one.

1131
01:35:57.552 --> 01:36:00.953
I'm not what you are.  And not what you intended.

1132
01:36:03.161 --> 01:36:04.654
So there may be no way to make you trust me.

1133
01:36:04.728 --> 01:36:05.952
But we need to go.

1134
01:36:21.442 --> 01:36:22.442
Right.

1135
01:36:23.516 --> 01:36:24.516
Well done.

1136
01:36:26.513 --> 01:36:27.513
Three minutes.

1137
01:36:28.451 --> 01:36:29.675
Get what you need.

1138
01:36:45.868 --> 01:36:47.161
Good evening. boss.

1139
01:36:51.808 --> 01:36:55.289
No way we all get through this.  If even one tin soldier is left standing. we've lost.

1140
01:36:56.212 --> 01:36:58.957
- It's gonna be blood on the floor.
- I got no plans tomorrow night.

1141
01:36:59.083 --> 01:37:02.913
I get first crack at the big guy.  Iron Man's the one he's waiting for.

1142
01:37:03.651 --> 01:37:06.032
That's true. he hates you the most.

1143
01:37:10.358 --> 01:37:15.258
Ultron knows we're coming.  Odds are we'll be riding into heavy fire.

1144
01:37:15.653 --> 01:37:20.007
And that's what we signed up for.  But the people of Sokovia. they didn't.

1145
01:37:20.938 --> 01:37:24.538
So our priority is getting them out.

1146
01:37:24.740 --> 01:37:28.333
We're under attack.  Clear the city. now.

1147
01:37:35.914 --> 01:37:37.207
Get off your asses.

1148
01:37:38.287 --> 01:37:43.169
All they want is to live their lives in peace.  And that's not going to happen today.

1149
01:37:43.825 --> 01:37:48.145
But we can do our best to protect them.  And we can get the job done.

1150
01:37:51.166 --> 01:37:53.683
We find out what Ultron's been building.

1151
01:37:54.289 --> 01:37:55.445
We find Romanoff.

1152
01:37:56.872 --> 01:37:58.165
and we clear the field.

1153
01:37:59.025 --> 01:38:00.998
Keep the fight between us.

1154
01:38:08.551 --> 01:38:12.824
Ultron thinks we're monsters and we're what's wrong with the world.

1155
01:38:13.656 --> 01:38:18.456
This isn't just about beating him.  It's about whether he's right.

1156
01:38:24.836 --> 01:38:27.660
Natasha!  Natasha!

1157
01:38:28.704 --> 01:38:29.704
Bruce?

1158
01:38:31.471 --> 01:38:32.471
You all right?

1159
01:38:32.708 --> 01:38:33.408
Yeah.

1160
01:38:33.477 --> 01:38:35.370
The team's in the city. it's about to light up.

1161
01:38:35.414 --> 01:38:37.347
I don't suppose you found a key lying around somewhere?

1162
01:38:37.911 --> 01:38:40.011
Yeah.  I did.

1163
01:38:46.192 --> 01:38:47.185
So what's our play?

1164
01:38:47.525 --> 01:38:50.125
- I'm here to get you to safety.
- Job's not finished.

1165
01:38:50.610 --> 01:38:57.005
We could help with the evacuation. but I can't be in a fight near civilians.  And you've done plenty.

1166
01:38:59.035 --> 01:39:00.259
Our fight is over.

1167
01:39:02.206 --> 01:39:03.635
So we just disappear?

1168
01:39:09.047 --> 01:39:10.047
Come on.

1169
01:39:14.623 --> 01:39:18.384
Your man's in the church. boss.  I think he's waiting for you.

1170
01:39:23.227 --> 01:39:24.996
Come to confess your sins?

1171
01:39:25.628 --> 01:39:27.241
I don't know. how much time you got?

1172
01:39:27.242 --> 01:39:28.642
More than you.

1173
01:39:29.365 --> 01:39:32.665
Uhhh.  Have you been juicing?  On a Vibranium cocktail?

1174
01:39:33.634 --> 01:39:36.027
You're looking...I don't wanna say. puffy...

1175
01:39:36.102 --> 01:39:37.190
You're stalling to protect the people.

1176
01:39:38.121 --> 01:39:41.046
Well. that is the mission.  Did you forget?

1177
01:39:41.410 --> 01:39:44.719
I've moved beyond your mission.  I'm free.

1178
01:39:48.587 --> 01:39:49.587
What.

1179
01:39:50.316 --> 01:39:52.969
you think you're the only one stalling?

1180
01:39:53.787 --> 01:39:56.800
There's the rest of the Vibranium.  Function: still unclear.

1181
01:39:56.928 --> 01:39:58.697
This is how you end. Tony.

1182
01:39:59.364 --> 01:40:01.065
This is peace in my time.

1183
01:40:17.833 --> 01:40:18.833
Go!

1184
01:40:23.755 --> 01:40:24.755
Get off the bridge!

1185
01:40:29.894 --> 01:40:30.894
Run!

1186
01:40:32.627 --> 01:40:33.627
Ultron!

1187
01:40:40.034 --> 01:40:43.571
My Vision.  They really did take everything from me.

1188
01:40:44.039 --> 01:40:47.780
- You set the terms. you can change them.
- All right.

1189
01:40:49.477 --> 01:40:50.477
Ahhh!

1190
01:41:11.267 --> 01:41:12.628
FRIDAY!  The Vision?

1191
01:41:12.668 --> 01:41:17.278
Boss. it's working.  He's burning Ultron out of the 'net. he won't escape through there.

1192
01:41:20.910 --> 01:41:21.998
You shut me out!

1193
01:41:23.312 --> 01:41:24.468
You think I care?

1194
01:41:26.395 --> 01:41:29.252
You take away my world. I take away yours.

1195
01:41:37.694 --> 01:41:39.687
Whoa!  What's this?

1196
01:41:44.667 --> 01:41:45.667
Run!

1197
01:41:54.909 --> 01:41:55.909
Get back. get back!

1198
01:42:14.933 --> 01:42:17.654
- FRIDAY?
- Sokovia's going for a ride.

1199
01:42:30.314 --> 01:42:37.011
Do you see?  The beauty of it.  The inevitability.

1200
01:42:37.188 --> 01:42:40.653
You rise. only to fall.

1201
01:42:43.360 --> 01:42:51.319
You. Avengers. you are my meteor. my swift and terrible sword and the earth will crack with the weight of your failure.

1202
01:42:54.136 --> 01:42:58.150
Purge me from your computers. turn my own flesh against me.

1203
01:42:58.540 --> 01:42:59.696
It means nothing.

1204
01:43:00.117 --> 01:43:05.883
When the dust settles. the only thing living in this world will be metal.

1205
01:43:10.752 --> 01:43:11.752
We gotta move.

1206
01:43:12.322 --> 01:43:13.531
You're not going to turn green?

1207
01:43:13.893 --> 01:43:16.826
I've got a compelling reason to not lose my cool.

1208
01:43:16.893 --> 01:43:17.893
I adore you.

1209
01:43:26.302 --> 01:43:28.003
But I need the other guy.

1210
01:43:33.375 --> 01:43:34.599
Let's finish the job.

1211
01:43:51.724 --> 01:43:54.969
- I really hope this makes us even.
- (grunt)

1212
01:43:55.265 --> 01:43:57.821
- Now go be a hero.
- Raaar!

1213
01:44:05.780 --> 01:44:10.018
The Vibranium core has got a magnetic field. that's what's keeping the rock together.

1214
01:44:10.048 --> 01:44:14.410
- If it drops?
- Right now the impact would kill thousands.  Once it gets high enough...

1215
01:44:14.411 --> 01:44:15.635
...global extinction.

1216
01:44:19.556 --> 01:44:21.869
That building's not clear. its tenth floor.

1217
01:44:26.881 --> 01:44:27.881
Hi.

1218
01:44:29.231 --> 01:44:31.128
Okay.  Get in the tub!

1219
01:44:38.374 --> 01:44:41.163
I got airborne. heading up to the bridge.

1220
01:44:42.353 --> 01:44:43.986
Cap. you got incoming.

1221
01:44:44.080 --> 01:44:45.781
Incoming already came in.

1222
01:44:48.250 --> 01:44:51.247
Stark. you worry about bringing the city back down safely.

1223
01:44:51.522 --> 01:44:54.727
The rest of us have one job: tear these things apart.

1224
01:44:54.827 --> 01:45:00.245
You get hurt. hurt 'em back.  You get killed. walk it off.

1225
01:45:35.330 --> 01:45:36.330
Go. go. move!

1226
01:45:41.603 --> 01:45:43.403
How could I let this happen?

1227
01:45:43.572 --> 01:45:44.865
Hey. hey. you okay?

1228
01:45:45.307 --> 01:45:46.327
This is all our fault.

1229
01:45:46.340 --> 01:45:47.128
Hey. look at me.

1230
01:45:47.197 --> 01:45:49.598
It's your fault. it's everyone's fault. who cares.

1231
01:45:49.680 --> 01:45:51.041
Are you up for this?

1232
01:45:51.247 --> 01:45:52.247
Are you?

1233
01:45:53.028 --> 01:45:56.633
Look. I just need to know. 'cause the city i-. is flying.

1234
01:45:56.854 --> 01:46:02.472
Okay. look. the city is flying. we're fighting an army of robots. and I have a bow and arrow.

1235
01:46:02.478 --> 01:46:04.179
None of this makes sense.

1236
01:46:06.662 --> 01:46:10.335
But I'm going back out there because of my job.  Okay?

1237
01:46:10.400 --> 01:46:12.441
And I can't do my job and babysit.

1238
01:46:12.933 --> 01:46:18.612
It doesn't matter what you did. or what you were.  If you go out there. you fight. and you fight to kill.

1239
01:46:18.638 --> 01:46:24.311
Stay in here. you're good. I'll send your brother to come find you. but if you step out that door.

1240
01:46:24.813 --> 01:46:26.106
you are an Avenger.

1241
01:46:30.821 --> 01:46:32.250
All right. good chat.

1242
01:46:35.357 --> 01:46:37.058
Yeah. the city is flying.

1243
01:47:10.993 --> 01:47:11.993
I got you!

1244
01:47:12.897 --> 01:47:13.985
Just look at me.

1245
01:47:20.368 --> 01:47:22.001
You can't save them all.

1246
01:47:23.414 --> 01:47:24.434
You'll never...

1247
01:47:25.097 --> 01:47:27.818
"You'll never" what?  You didn't finish!

1248
01:47:31.515 --> 01:47:33.080
What. were you napping?

1249
01:47:55.134 --> 01:47:56.434
Thor!

1250
01:47:57.807 --> 01:47:59.236
You are bothering me.

1251
01:48:08.619 --> 01:48:09.619
Ow!

1252
01:48:11.188 --> 01:48:12.188
Uh...

1253
01:48:35.544 --> 01:48:39.321
- All right. we're all clear here.
- We are not clear!  We are very not clear!

1254
01:48:42.116 --> 01:48:43.817
All right. coming to you.

1255
01:48:43.988 --> 01:48:45.144
Keep up. old man.

1256
01:48:48.592 --> 01:48:49.816
Nobody would know.

1257
01:48:50.708 --> 01:48:51.708
Nobody.

1258
01:48:53.259 --> 01:49:00.046
Yeah. last I saw him. and Ultron was sitting on him. uh...yeah. he'll be missed. that quick little bastard.  I miss him already.

1259
01:49:14.814 --> 01:49:16.634
Hold your fire!

1260
01:49:25.927 --> 01:49:26.927
Romanoff!

1261
01:49:27.463 --> 01:49:28.463
Thanks.

1262
01:49:38.007 --> 01:49:43.504
The anti-gravs are rigged to flip.  Touch 'em. they'll go full reverse thrust.  The city's not coming down slow.

1263
01:49:43.544 --> 01:49:45.454
The spire's Vibranium.  If I get Thor to hit it...

1264
01:49:46.117 --> 01:49:49.017
It'll crack. but that's not enough. the impact would still be devastating.

1265
01:49:49.552 --> 01:49:52.758
Maybe if we could cap the other end. keep the atomic action doubling back.

1266
01:49:53.136 --> 01:49:55.109
That could vaporize the city.  And everyone on it.

1267
01:50:02.480 --> 01:50:04.197
The next wave's gonna hit any minute.

1268
01:50:04.201 --> 01:50:05.802
What have you got. Stark?

1269
01:50:05.865 --> 01:50:09.538
Well. nothing great.  Maybe a way to blow up the city.

1270
01:50:09.840 --> 01:50:12.262
That'll keep it from impacting the surface if you guys can get clear.

1271
01:50:12.308 --> 01:50:15.133
I asked for a solution. not an escape plan.

1272
01:50:15.210 --> 01:50:17.271
Impact radius is getting bigger every second.

1273
01:50:17.310 --> 01:50:19.827
We're going to have to make a choice.

1274
01:50:20.051 --> 01:50:23.625
Cap. these people are going nowhere.  If Stark finds a way to blow this rock...

1275
01:50:24.386 --> 01:50:25.687
Not 'til everyone's safe.

1276
01:50:25.687 --> 01:50:28.487
Everyone up here versus everyone down there?  There's no math there.

1277
01:50:28.490 --> 01:50:30.490
I'm not leaving this rock with one civilian on it.

1278
01:50:30.794 --> 01:50:32.767
I didn't say we should leave.

1279
01:50:34.459 --> 01:50:36.092
There's worse ways to go.

1280
01:50:41.272 --> 01:50:44.197
Where else am I gonna get a view like this?

1281
01:50:45.491 --> 01:50:50.191
Glad you like the view. Romanoff.  It's about to get better.

1282
01:51:13.502 --> 01:51:19.755
Nice. right?  I pulled her out of mothballs with a couple of old friends.  She's dusty. but she'll do.

1283
01:51:19.772 --> 01:51:21.373
Fury. you son of a bitch.

1284
01:51:21.373 --> 01:51:23.834
Oooh!  You kiss your mother with that mouth?

1285
01:51:24.114 --> 01:51:26.091
Altitude is 18.000 and climbing.

1286
01:51:26.180 --> 01:51:32.580
Lifeboats secure to deploy.  Disengage in 3. 2...take 'em out.

1287
01:51:41.829 --> 01:51:42.849
This is SHIELD?

1288
01:51:43.931 --> 01:51:46.448
This is what SHIELD's supposed to be.

1289
01:51:48.271 --> 01:51:49.564
This is not so bad.

1290
01:51:52.941 --> 01:51:53.941
Let's load 'em up.

1291
01:51:59.880 --> 01:52:02.866
Sir. we have multiple bogies converging on our starboard flank.

1292
01:52:03.262 --> 01:52:04.691
Show 'em what we got.

1293
01:52:05.085 --> 01:52:06.085
You're up.

1294
01:52:11.727 --> 01:52:14.448
Yes!  Now this is gonna be a good story.

1295
01:52:17.334 --> 01:52:19.307
Yup.  If you live to tell it.

1296
01:52:19.636 --> 01:52:21.577
You think I can't hold my own?

1297
01:52:21.650 --> 01:52:23.771
We get through this. I'll hold your own.

1298
01:52:23.807 --> 01:52:25.508
You had to make it weird.

1299
01:52:29.447 --> 01:52:31.847
Donovan!  I got about 50 to 100 more coming in after this group.

1300
01:52:33.918 --> 01:52:35.406
All right. let's go!

1301
01:52:48.968 --> 01:52:51.197
All right. here we go.  Here we go. let's move.

1302
01:52:51.299 --> 01:52:52.299
Let's go everyone!

1303
01:52:55.228 --> 01:53:01.963
Number six boat is topped and locked.  Or. uh. or stocked. topped. it...it's uh. full of people.

1304
01:53:03.610 --> 01:53:04.610
Incoming!

1305
01:53:07.424 --> 01:53:08.424
Oh. God!

1306
01:53:19.294 --> 01:53:20.791
You think you're saving anyone?

1307
01:53:22.395 --> 01:53:27.983
I turn that key and drop this rock a little early and it's still billions dead.  Even you can't stop that.

1308
01:53:28.203 --> 01:53:36.902
I am Thor. son of Odin. and as long as there is life in my breast. I am...running out of things to say!  Are you ready?

1309
01:53:43.720 --> 01:53:45.525
It's terribly well balanced.

1310
01:53:45.573 --> 01:53:49.791
Well. if there's too much weight. you lose power on the swing. so.

1311
01:53:50.104 --> 01:53:52.825
I got it!  Create a heat seal.  I can...

1312
01:53:54.386 --> 01:53:58.536
- I can supercharge the spire from below.
- Running numbers.

1313
01:54:07.810 --> 01:54:11.231
- A heat seal could work with enough power.
- Thor. I got a plan!

1314
01:54:11.279 --> 01:54:14.144
We're out of time.  They're coming for the core.

1315
01:54:14.149 --> 01:54:16.682
- Rhodey. get the rest of the people on board that carrier.
- On it.

1316
01:54:16.862 --> 01:54:19.311
Avengers. time to work for a living.

1317
01:54:28.231 --> 01:54:29.731
- You good?
- Yeah.

1318
01:54:30.453 --> 01:54:31.453
Romanoff?

1319
01:54:31.935 --> 01:54:34.676
You and Banner better not be playing hide the zucchini.

1320
01:54:34.938 --> 01:54:37.638
Relax. Shell-head.  Not all of us can fly.

1321
01:54:43.078 --> 01:54:45.167
- What's the drill?
- This is the drill.

1322
01:54:45.248 --> 01:54:47.348
If Ultron gets a hand on the core. we lose.

1323
01:54:51.819 --> 01:54:53.219
Is that the best you can do?

1324
01:55:03.266 --> 01:55:04.286
You had to ask.

1325
01:55:05.098 --> 01:55:06.867
This is the best I can do.

1326
01:55:07.936 --> 01:55:12.086
This is exactly what I wanted.  All of you against all of me.

1327
01:55:13.109 --> 01:55:15.626
How can you possibly hope to stop me?

1328
01:55:16.976 --> 01:55:20.321
Like the old man said.  Together.

1329
01:55:20.682 --> 01:55:22.282
Raaarrrr!!!

1330
01:56:47.838 --> 01:56:51.438
Uhh!  You know. with the benefit of hindsight....

1331
01:56:56.034 --> 01:56:57.034
Rarrrr!

1332
01:57:00.718 --> 01:57:02.459
They'll try to leave the city.

1333
01:57:02.485 --> 01:57:04.394
We can't let 'em. not even one.  Rhodey!

1334
01:57:04.412 --> 01:57:06.912
I'm on it.  Oh no. I didn't say you could leave.

1335
01:57:07.589 --> 01:57:09.358
War Machine. comin' at you. right a-...

1336
01:57:16.126 --> 01:57:17.126
Okay. what?

1337
01:57:17.431 --> 01:57:21.055
We gotta move out.  Even I can tell the air is getting thin.  You guys get to the boats...

1338
01:57:21.124 --> 01:57:23.124
I'll sweep for stragglers. be right behind you.

1339
01:57:23.236 --> 01:57:24.497
What about the core?

1340
01:57:24.806 --> 01:57:29.094
I'll protect it.  It's my job.

1341
01:57:29.978 --> 01:57:31.778
Nat.  Let's go.

1342
01:57:36.120 --> 01:57:40.270
- Get the people on the boats.
- I'm not going to leave you.
- I can handle these.

1343
01:57:42.121 --> 01:57:44.346
Come back for me when everyone else is off. not before.

1344
01:57:44.358 --> 01:57:45.878
- Mmm.
- You understand?

1345
01:57:47.926 --> 01:57:50.047
You know. I'm 12 minutes older than you.

1346
01:57:50.323 --> 01:57:51.323
Heh. Go.

1347
01:57:52.966 --> 01:57:59.156
- Boss. power levels are way below...
- Re-route everything.  We've got one shot at this.

1348
01:58:01.208 --> 01:58:03.861
I know what I need to do.  The dining room!

1349
01:58:04.546 --> 01:58:09.512
If I knock out that east wall. it'll make a nice work space for Laura. huh.

1350
01:58:09.598 --> 01:58:12.259
Put up some baffling. she can't hear the kids running around. what do you think?

1351
01:58:12.406 --> 01:58:14.491
You guys always eat in the kitchen anyway.

1352
01:58:14.588 --> 01:58:16.561
No one eats in a dining room.

1353
01:58:19.026 --> 01:58:20.026
Raarrrr!

1354
01:58:21.263 --> 01:58:23.168
We don't have a lot of time.

1355
01:58:23.196 --> 01:58:24.965
So get your ass on a boat.

1356
01:58:37.681 --> 01:58:38.681
Hey big guy.

1357
01:58:40.884 --> 01:58:42.449
Sun's getting real low.

1358
01:58:42.659 --> 01:58:46.408
You're safe now.  It'll be okay. buckle up...

1359
01:58:48.323 --> 01:58:50.016
...secure your gear. find a seat...

1360
01:58:50.092 --> 01:58:51.092
Costel?

1361
01:58:52.526 --> 01:58:53.526
We were in the market.

1362
01:58:54.295 --> 01:58:57.088
Costel?!

1363
01:59:09.679 --> 01:59:11.872
Thor. I'm gonna need you back in the church.

1364
01:59:11.913 --> 01:59:13.614
- Is this the last of them?
- Yeah.

1365
01:59:14.017 --> 01:59:15.017
Everyone else is on the carrier.

1366
01:59:15.048 --> 01:59:20.113
- Y'know. if this works. we maybe don't walk away.
- Maybe not.

1367
01:59:39.175 --> 01:59:44.921
(singing) I have no strings. so I have fun.  I'm not tied up to anyone.

1368
01:59:47.018 --> 01:59:48.311
C'mon. I'll help you up.

1369
02:00:20.924 --> 02:00:22.625
You didn't see that coming.

1370
02:01:18.871 --> 02:01:20.368
Oh. for god's sake...!

1371
02:01:37.761 --> 02:01:39.061
Costel!

1372
02:01:50.938 --> 02:01:52.162
No. no.  I'm fine.

1373
02:01:55.445 --> 02:01:56.874
But it's been a long day.

1374
02:02:11.995 --> 02:02:12.995
Wanda.

1375
02:02:14.000 --> 02:02:15.973
If you stay here. you'll die.

1376
02:02:18.299 --> 02:02:19.499
I just did.

1377
02:02:20.570 --> 02:02:21.999
Do you know how it felt?

1378
02:02:36.547 --> 02:02:37.971
It felt like that.

1379
02:03:13.458 --> 02:03:14.914
Thor. on my mark.

1380
02:03:30.771 --> 02:03:31.971
Now!

1381
02:03:59.151 --> 02:04:00.351
Hey big guy.

1382
02:04:01.370 --> 02:04:02.570
We did it.

1383
02:04:02.835 --> 02:04:04.196
The job's finished.

1384
02:04:05.072 --> 02:04:07.872
Now I need you to turn this bird around. okay?

1385
02:04:12.248 --> 02:04:16.817
We can't track you in stealth mode. so help me out.

1386
02:04:17.749 --> 02:04:18.769
I need you t...

1387
02:04:50.488 --> 02:04:51.488
Oh. dear.

1388
02:05:03.596 --> 02:05:04.596
You're afraid.

1389
02:05:05.730 --> 02:05:08.430
- Of you?
- Of death.

1390
02:05:09.070 --> 02:05:10.431
You're the last one.

1391
02:05:11.464 --> 02:05:13.913
You were supposed to be the last.

1392
02:05:13.938 --> 02:05:17.939
Stark asked for a savior. and settled for a slave.

1393
02:05:19.078 --> 02:05:21.595
I suppose we're both disappointments.

1394
02:05:21.647 --> 02:05:24.847
Ha ha ha ha.  I suppose we are.

1395
02:05:25.788 --> 02:05:26.888
Humans are odd.

1396
02:05:28.987 --> 02:05:32.592
They think order and chaos are somehow opposites. and

1397
02:05:34.325 --> 02:05:36.298
try to control what won't be.

1398
02:05:37.332 --> 02:05:39.849
But there is grace in their failings.

1399
02:05:40.219 --> 02:05:41.852
I think you missed that.

1400
02:05:42.835 --> 02:05:43.855
They're doomed.

1401
02:05:44.939 --> 02:05:45.939
Yes.

1402
02:05:49.642 --> 02:05:52.847
But a thing isn't beautiful because it lasts.

1403
02:05:54.899 --> 02:05:57.212
It's a privilege to be among them.

1404
02:05:57.549 --> 02:05:59.182
You're unbearably naive.

1405
02:06:00.421 --> 02:06:01.458
Well.

1406
02:06:03.122 --> 02:06:04.551
I was born yesterday.

1407
02:06:59.954 --> 02:07:00.954
(chatter)

1408
02:07:18.036 --> 02:07:19.465
Say hi to Auntie Nat.

1409
02:07:21.233 --> 02:07:22.233
Fat.

1410
02:07:23.307 --> 02:07:27.797
One of our tech boys flagged this. splashed down in the Banda Sea.

1411
02:07:29.844 --> 02:07:35.766
could be the Quinjet.  But with Stark's stealth tech. we still can't track the damn thing.

1412
02:07:35.783 --> 02:07:36.783
Right.

1413
02:07:37.984 --> 02:07:40.433
Probably jumped out and swam to Fiji.

1414
02:07:41.122 --> 02:07:42.619
He'll send a postcard.

1415
02:07:43.558 --> 02:07:44.851
"Wish you were here."

1416
02:07:47.130 --> 02:07:49.987
You sent me to recruit him. way back when.

1417
02:07:51.430 --> 02:07:54.355
Did you know then what was going to happen?

1418
02:07:56.773 --> 02:08:01.603
You never know.  You hope for the best and make do with what you get.

1419
02:08:03.209 --> 02:08:04.502
I got a great team.

1420
02:08:05.546 --> 02:08:07.043
Nothing lasts forever.

1421
02:08:08.148 --> 02:08:13.658
Trouble. Ms. Romanoff.  No matter who wins or loses. trouble still comes 'round.

1422
02:08:18.023 --> 02:08:20.169
- The rules have changed.
- We're dealing with something new.

1423
02:08:20.261 --> 02:08:23.317
- Well. the Vision's artificial intelligence.
- A machine.

1424
02:08:23.797 --> 02:08:26.599
- So it doesn't count.
- No.  It's not. like. a person lifting the hammer.

1425
02:08:26.697 --> 02:08:29.297
- Right.  Different rules for us.
- Nice guy.  But artificial.
- Thank you.

1426
02:08:29.471 --> 02:08:33.008
If he can wield the hammer. he can keep the Mind Stone.

1427
02:08:33.139 --> 02:08:34.908
It's safe with the Vision.

1428
02:08:35.141 --> 02:08:37.862
And these days. safe is in short supply.

1429
02:08:40.183 --> 02:08:44.346
- But if you put the hammer in an elevator...
- It would still go up.
- Elevator's not worthy.

1430
02:08:44.386 --> 02:08:45.671
I'm going to miss these little talks of ours.

1431
02:08:45.751 --> 02:08:47.316
Not if you don't leave.

1432
02:08:47.554 --> 02:08:48.710
I have no choice.

1433
02:08:49.453 --> 02:08:55.636
The Mind Stone is the fourth of the Infinity Stones to show up in the last few years.  That's not a coincidence.

1434
02:08:56.332 --> 02:08:59.232
Someone has been playing an intricate game and has made pawns of us.

1435
02:08:59.430 --> 02:09:02.887
- Once all these pieces are in position...
- Triple Yahtzee?

1436
02:09:02.938 --> 02:09:04.627
You think you can find out what's coming?

1437
02:09:04.674 --> 02:09:05.674
I do.

1438
02:09:06.508 --> 02:09:10.454
Besides this one. there's nothing that can't be explained.

1439
02:09:18.078 --> 02:09:21.071
That man has no regard for lawn maintenance.

1440
02:09:23.458 --> 02:09:24.995
I'm gonna miss him though.

1441
02:09:25.094 --> 02:09:29.584
And you're gonna miss me.  There's gonna be a lot of manful tears.

1442
02:09:29.630 --> 02:09:31.127
I will miss you. Tony.

1443
02:09:31.933 --> 02:09:34.722
Yeah?  Well. it's time for me to tap out.

1444
02:09:36.237 --> 02:09:41.904
Maybe I should take a page out of Barton's book and build Pepper a farm.  Hope nobody blows it up.

1445
02:09:41.974 --> 02:09:42.862
The simple life.

1446
02:09:42.908 --> 02:09:44.064
You'll get there one day.

1447
02:09:44.747 --> 02:09:52.847
I don't know.  Family. stability.  The guy who wanted all that went in the ice 75 years ago.

1448
02:09:54.157 --> 02:09:56.198
I think someone else came out.

1449
02:10:00.361 --> 02:10:01.361
You all right?

1450
02:10:02.862 --> 02:10:03.862
I'm home.

1451
02:10:13.009 --> 02:10:14.922
You want to keep staring at the wall. or do you want to go to work?

1452
02:10:14.978 --> 02:10:17.631
I mean. it's a pretty interesting wall.

1453
02:10:17.679 --> 02:10:21.097
I thought you and Tony were still gazing into each other's eyes.

1454
02:10:21.100 --> 02:10:22.120
How do we look?

1455
02:10:22.183 --> 02:10:24.971
- Well. we're not the '27 Yankees.
- We've got some hitters.

1456
02:10:25.950 --> 02:10:30.440
- They're good.  They're not a team.
- Let's beat 'em into shape.

1457
02:10:48.671 --> 02:10:50.471
Avengers...!

1458
02:10:50.685 --> 02:10:55.685
SPOILER COMING UP -

1459
02:10:55.722 --> 02:11:00.722
